('c84a08c6-1df1-4ce3-978d-fdfaa230fca6','C.Viper','Neutral Jump HK','','8HK','normal',10,7,NULL,6,11,800,'M','','Furthest horizontal range and strongest horizontal hitbox priority of all of C. Viper''s jump normals (although the effective horizontal range is very limited due to only being accessible from a Neutral jump); Projectile invincible on lower body (legs) on frames 10-19',19,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('592e9565-a6df-4ec8-9caa-a48e06e1b198','C.Viper','Viper Elbow','','6MP','normal',22,3,20,-3,2,600,'M','','Overhead; Crushes lows on frames 16-27 (not airborne or throw invincible)',20,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f0f5f324-d3fb-4038-8413-29594cd91548','C.Viper','Double Kick','','6HK','normal',11,3,16,-2,4,900,'H','','2 hits; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Useful approach tool from Drive Rush that grants a strike/throw mixup on block or a Crouch MP link on hit; Minimal pushback gives this a lot of uses cases on hit or block; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',21,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c9236fa2-3756-4a9c-a9e8-0c8a97accbee','C.Viper','High Impulse','','LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Grants a corner throw loop with forward dash (+7) or walking with manual timing; Can pressure with meaty Burning Kick + Double Burn (+2 oB): MK version makes the follow-up a true blockstring, while HK version leaves a small blockstring gap that can bait Drive Impact; Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',22,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('15ee3973-e24e-4934-b197-56dc68f86ade','C.Viper','Thunder Cradle','','4LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','No real oki after a corner side switch (but can pressure with Drive Rush normals); Can pressure with meaty LK Burning Kick into Double Burn (+2 oB) (punishable with wakeup Drive Impact, but opponent cannot DI punish the Double Burn); Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',23,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('08fe5bba-16b8-4b8c-a660-8de74d4a4f6f','C.Viper','Drive Impact: Viper Cannon','','HPHK','unique',26,2,35,-3,NULL,800,'H','','2 hits of armor on frames 1-27; Damages opponents Drive Gauge on Block (1/2 bar) | Hit (1 bar) | Counter-Hit (1.25 bar) | Punish Counter (1.5 bar); Knocks down on hit; Crumples on Punish Counter or after absorbing at least 1 attack during start-up (+21 frames before the crumple state goes airborne, followed by airborne state on frames 22-46 before they are grounded) which counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; If the armor absorbs an attack it slows the overall start-up by 1F (27F total instead of 26F); Pushes the opponent far back on hit or block and causes a wall splat if they hit the wall; Wall Splat on block adds 20% damage penalty on the next hit; Wall splats on hit or during Burnout counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; Wall Splat puts opponent into a special juggle state where the next move juggles them even if it doesn''t normally (similar juggle rules as from Drive Rush); Does not cause wall splat if combo''d into from other moves or unblockable setups (Lock); Puts airborne opponents into a long spinning free juggle state when hit as a Punish Counter; Regular KDA without a Wall Splat: +35 KD; Corner wall splat on HIT: +65 KD | Block: +72 HKD; KDA can vary greatly depending on how high the opponent wall splats (higher KDA the higher they wall splat); Can clash with other Drive Impacts if they collide on the same active frame (start at exactly the same time); Costs 1 bar of Drive Gauge; The scrub killer',24,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e384a629-00fc-4b73-a43a-de1cbd948af3','C.Viper','Drive Reversal: Counter Spark','','6HPHK','unique',20,3,26,-6,NULL,500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-22 (frames 1-20 when used on wake-up as a Reversal); Armor Break (blows through all armor like Drive Impact); Can be performed during blockstun or from a successful parry (trying to Drive Reversal after the blockstun is over will result in a Drive Impact); Can also be performed during wake-up as a Reversal, doing it this way speeds up the start-up frames by 2 frames (18F start-up instead of 20F); Drive Reversal immediately removes the current blockstun you''re in and starts the attack; Causes a 4F screen freeze that occurs after the 6th start-up frame, which can mess up the opponents input timing, or enable them to do a simple input OS to counter the Drive Reversal; Safe on block (-2) when used against an opponent currently in Burnout; Costs 2 bars of Drive Gauge',25,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d07b0391-439c-4048-b9e1-dbf62de784ba','C.Viper','Drive Parry','','MPMK','unique',1,12,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Parries all strikes and projectiles (high and low) from frame 1; 12F parry window (can hold the parry to extend the parry window); Perfect Parry occurs on the first 2 active frames (cannot achieve Perfect Parry if you buffer into parry by holding it during Reversal windows; Perfect Parries have to be timed properly); Can still hold charge directions during Parry; Can block during the recovery frames of a regular parry (can still get hit during the recovery frames if you don''t block correctly); Getting thrown or hit at any point during the recovery frames of a whiffed parry attempt results in a Punish Counter; Successfully parrying a move puts you into the same amount of blockstun as that move would regularly do on block (but a Perfect Parry has only 1F of recovery); Throw invincible during the recovery of a successful parry (just like during blockstun); Perfect Parrying a strike has only 1F of recovery and disables the opponent from canceling their attack (basically a guaranteed punish opportunity); After a successful Perfect Parry, you suffer a 50% penalty to your Damage, Drive Gauge Generation, and Drive Gauge Damage on any of your following attacks when punishing the opponent (in addition, both you and the opponent suffer a 20% penalty to their Super Meter gain during this period); Fully invincible for 6F after a successful Perfect Parry against a strike, during which period you can cancel into anything you want and it carries over the brief invincibility frames; Perfect Parrying projectiles puts you into fixed 10 frames of recovery and applies the same 50% scaling penalties (and 20% Super Meter penalty) on your following attacks when punishing the opponent; Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will result in a regular parry for the strike attack (effectively ignoring the projectile''s hitstop / blockstun); Perfect Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will give a screen freeze like you Perfect Parried a Strike, but still give you 10F recovery as if you had Perfect Parried a Projectile; Can cancel into Drive Rush during active frames 3 and onward (fastest Drive Rush method is to buffer a forward input before doing parry + forward again); Can cancel into Drive Reversal from a successful parry (just like you can normally during blockstun); Costs 1/2 bar Drive Gauge (continues to deplete Drive Gauge as you hold the Parry); You lose the parry if you go into Burnout from the Drive Gauge cost; Rewards 1 bar Drive Gauge (1/2 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a strike; Rewards 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge (0 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a projectile; Rewards 2 bars of Drive Gauge (1.5 bars total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successful parrying a Drive Impact; Successfully parrying a strike attack splits the regular block pushback between both players (while Perfect Parrying a strike removes all of its pushback); Successfully parrying a projectile or Drive Impact reduces the pushback of it by half (while Perfect Parrying a projectile or Drive Impact removes all of its pushback); Your hurtbox and throw box expand slightly towards the opponent for the entire duration of the Parry (Throw box extension starts instantly on frame 1, while the Hurtbox extension starts on frame 3, after the initial 2F Perfect Parry window); Parrying while crouching maintains a regular crouch hurtbox for the first 2 frames of the parry (during the initial Perfect Parry window)',26,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('0c757ad5-2177-4cce-9abf-ee8f85cec44e','C.Viper','Drive Rush','','MPMK / 66 (cancel)','unique',9,45,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Dashes forward and enhances the next normal used out of the Drive Rush with +4 extra hitstun / blockstun (some moves also get unique properties enhanced such as juggle state); The +4 bonus frame advantage gained from a Drive Rush enhanced move also stacks with any bonus frame advantage that move may have gained from Counter-Hit or Punish Counter; Cancelable into from special cancelable grounded normals; Drive Rush maintains buffers (freezes the buffer window) during it start-up and freeze frames - This allows players to do things normally not possible within the normal buffer windows, such as Drive Rushing into a charge special; The initial freeze frames that occur when a Drive Rush happens eats the opponents inputs; Framedata shown in parentheses refers to the Drive Rush version used from a Parry; Drive Rush recovery frames is only 24F total (23F if done from a Parry) - but the enhanced dash itself is 46F total (45F if done from Parry) and you can cancel it as early as frame 9 (frame 11 if done from a Parry); You stop building any form of Drive Gauge on your attacks after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (but you still continue to build drive gauge as normal if you did Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Applies extra damage scaling penalty after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (no damage scaling if you use Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Costs 3 bars of Drive Gauge if canceled into from a move; Costs 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge if canceled into from Parry (for a total of 1 bar of Drive Gauge when you factor in the initial 1/2 bar cost of the Parry)',27,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1ea31588-f140-4ea7-af7c-c70bfd6fa503','C.Viper','Taunt','','5PPPKKK','unique',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',28,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('bff545d8-15de-4214-aa3e-c48bae49943b','C.Viper','LP Thunder Dash','','214LP','special',17,4,23,-4,1,900,'H','su3','Upper body is projectile invincible on frames 14-20; Crouch size hurtboxes on frames 14-43 (but still counts as in Standing state); Can be used to slip past certain Projectiles (C. Viper can get clipped in the back by the slower Projectiles) and potentially convert into a full combo on Punish Counter; Solid range for a neutral tool but must be spaced to remain safe on block; Does not count as a Low attack (despite looking like it might); Startup is cancelable into feint after 12F; Cancelable into Tracer Combination (f+PP) on hit or block',29,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5af62dc6-c3b1-4349-929c-a38dbada643d','C.Viper','MP Thunder Dash','','214MP','special',16,4,22,-3,1,900,'H','su3','Combos naturally from Stand LK; Less range than LP version but is safer as a buffer tool; Startup is cancelable into feint after 8F; Cancelable into Tracer Combination (f+PP) on hit or block',30,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c7662832-6183-4e0c-b9d0-16048e483a5e','C.Viper','HP Thunder Dash','','214HP','special',7,10,15,-24,NULL,900,'H','','Invincible to airborne attacks on frames 1-9; Airborne on frames 9-31 (Forced Knockdown state); Combos naturally from light normals; Startup is cancelable into feint after 6F (gives the best advantage for combos and block pressure); The Feint version''s 6F anti-air invincibility can be used to effectively spot dodge certain airborne attacks from the opponent and get better Punish opportunities as a result (this usually requires precise timing and/or spacing); Cancelable into Tracer Combination (f+PP) on hit only (can whiff against high airborne opponents); Cannot hit cross-up (behind C. Viper); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',31,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('05d94bb5-b0d6-427c-8852-31aa936feeb5','C.Viper','OD Thunder Dash','','214PP','special',18,4,21,-2,NULL,1600,'H','su2, su3','2 hits; 1st hit has range in between LP/MP versions; Combos naturally from medium/heavy normals allowing a safe, easy hitconfirm into SA2 or SA3; Cannot perform a feint cancel or Tracer Combination follow-up; Great chip and pressure tool against Burnout (leaves C. Viper inside throw range at +2 on Block); Has an extremely disjointed forward hitbox that can beat most pokes when used at midrange; Sets up a KD +42 safe jump on grounded hit (can only reach with max range Jump MK if midscreen)',32,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8652d0f6-2aaf-41bc-9bc3-f77913271b5c','C.Viper','LP Tracer Combination','','214LP > 6PP','special',15,3,28,-15,NULL,1500,'H','su3','Follow-up maintains the Projectile invincibility and Crouch size hurtboxes on frames 1-17 (frames 14-37 overall); Both hits are a true blockstring; Only follow-up that can combo into SA3 on grounded opponents; Gives solid oki with Drive Rush or Dash + manually timed walk; No Drive gauge cost during SA1 install',33,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7f5f6ddb-3921-4346-aca5-62ecb6e6cd4a','C.Viper','MP Tracer Combination','','214MP > 6PP','special',21,4,25,-13,NULL,1500,'H','su3','Small gap between hits on block if not spaced out or connecting on last 2 active frames (risky -3 oB frame trap option to stop opponents from taking their turn); Cannot combo into SA3 on grounded opponents; Limited juggle OTG bounce on airborne opponents (allows combo into SA3 when juggled into); Gives the worst oki of all follow-ups on a grounded hit (-3 after dash); No Drive gauge cost during SA1 install',34,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c50f5496-64db-4625-9144-c54e5d726676','C.Viper','HP Tracer Combination','','214HP > 6PP','special',17,4,11,NULL,NULL,1400,'H','','Can only be performed on hit; Follow-up can whiff on high airborne opponents; Gives the best oki of all Thunder Dash follow-ups on hit; No Drive gauge cost during SA1 install',35,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('06b1144f-17cb-435c-a621-6aebde077d82','C.Viper','LK Burning Kick','','236LK','special',23,5,7,-2,NULL,900,'H','','Cannot hit cross-up; Airborne on frames 5-34 (Forced Knockdown state); Lower body is projectile invincible on frames 14-27; Shortest range version primarily useful for beating throw techs and crouching buttons (connects from about C. Viper''s max poke range); Very difficult to space for better advantage due to minimal forward movement during active frames; Higher float on Punish Counter (+5 KD advantage and combos into KK follow-up)',36,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a60368a1-4401-4241-a67e-968d3a03f8cb','C.Viper','MK Burning Kick','','236MK','special',25,5,7,-2,NULL,900,'H','','Cannot hit cross-up; Airborne on frames 5-36 (Forced Knockdown state); Lower body is projectile invincible on frames 16-29; Medium range version useful for crushing low pokes from outside their max range; Useful for approaching opponent while keeping C. Viper outside the opponent''s throw range on block; Higher float on Punish Counter (+5 KD advantage and combos into KK follow-up)',37,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('790862c0-6c37-4c61-bf95-666067e53ca6','C.Viper','HK Burning Kick','','236HK','special',27,5,7,-2,NULL,900,'H','','Cannot hit cross-up; Airborne on frames 5-38 (Forced Knockdown state); Lower body is projectile invincible on frames 18-31; Longest range version used for safe approaches from long range; Easiest version to space for better block advantage due to its forward movement (but more likely to end up inside the opponent''s throw range at -2); Higher float on Punish Counter (+5 KD advantage and combos into KK follow-up)',38,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d98b8453-03b6-4f4e-a67b-73199febacf1','C.Viper','OD Burning Kick','','236KK','special',8,3,8,-4,NULL,1500,'H','su2, su3','2 hits (cannot be interrupted on block); Cannot hit cross-up; Airborne on frames 11-43 (Forced Knockdown state); Recovery is cancelable into SA2/SA3 after 11F on hit or block; Very difficult to space safely in neutral (minimal forward movement during 2nd hit active frames); 2nd hit has the longest maximum range of all versions, but cannot avoid most standard projectiles',39,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2644b12a-936c-4237-a7bc-2dee0259ff5b','C.Viper','Knuckled Pursuit','','236K > PP','special',12,4,14,-15,NULL,1700,'H','','Combos naturally on hit; No Drive gauge cost during SA1 install; Higher KD Advantage if Burning Kick hits airborne opponent or lands as a Punish Counter (+1 extra KD Advantage on Punish Counter); Grants +9 KD Advantage when connecting on a grounded opponent after Burning Kick is absorbed by armor',40,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b8326dab-192a-4f0a-9cd7-6611bc1c5e7e','C.Viper','Double Burn','','236K > KK','special',21,5,3,2,NULL,600,'H','','Leaves C. Viper with advantage on block but does not combo on hit without a Punish Counter (KD +13 if follow-up whiffs); Leaves a 3F gap that can be interrupted with anti-air invincible moves or Drive Impact (true blockstring if opponent is in Burnout); If Burning Kick is blocked on a later active frame, the opponent can no longer punish with Drive Impact (forms a true blockstring on the final 2 active frames); No Drive gauge cost during SA1 install; An especially strong pressure & bully tool when the opponent is in Burnout; Knockdown Advantage varies greatly depending on opponents height from the ground (higher advantage the higher up in the air the opponent is) as well as how how late into the active frames the move connects; Grants +40 KD Advantage if this follow-up kick connects on a grounded opponent (like if the opponent doesn''t block this follow-up kick)',41,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f73d4b46-4dc5-4575-8ccf-4dae9e7bf4b6','C.Viper','LK Burning Kick (air)','','236LK (air)','special',22,7,13,-6,NULL,900,'H','','Can be input during neutral or forward jump (activates after 7 airborne frames at the earliest); Stops forward air momentum completely; Performs an alternate version out of High Jump (1F less blockstun but can activate after only 3 airborne frames for better advantage); Can hit cross-up; +8F extra landing recovery (21F) on whiff after crossing over the opponent; Forced Knockdown state while airborne; Frame Advantage on Hit or Block varies greatly depending on the angle, spacing and height from ground (higher advantage the closer to the ground C. Viper is when the move connects); Advantage on instant air (Tiger Knee) version at close range: KD +39 / -3 oB (regular jump) | KD +43 / 0 oB (Super Jump)',42,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f1e5e267-3ede-4c71-88a8-75835cc02c1d','C.Viper','MK Burning Kick (air)','','236MK (air)','special',20,7,13,-6,NULL,900,'H','','Can be input during neutral or forward jump (activates after 7 airborne frames at the earliest); Maintains some air momentum during forward jump; Performs an alternate version out of High Jump (1F less blockstun but can activate after only 3 airborne frames for better advantage); Can hit cross-up; +8F extra landing recovery (21F) on whiff after crossing over the opponent; Forced Knockdown state while airborne; Frame Advantage on Hit or Block varies greatly depending on the angle, spacing and height from ground (higher advantage the closer to the ground C. Viper is when the move connects); Advantage on instant air (Tiger Knee) version at close range: KD +40 / -2 oB (regular jump) | KD +43 / 0 oB (Super Jump); When performed from Seismo + SJC, this version allows C. Viper to juggle MP Thunder Dash + Tracer Combination for solid damage, corner carry, and oki',43,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c9b9490f-7735-4ca9-ac79-672110b79cc6','C.Viper','HK Burning Kick (air)','','236HK (air)','special',18,7,13,-6,NULL,900,'H','','Can be input during neutral or forward jump (activates after 7 airborne frames at the earliest); Maintains significant air momentum during forward jump; Performs an alternate version out of High Jump (1F less blockstun but can activate after only 3 airborne frames for better advantage); Can hit cross-up; +8F extra landing recovery (21F) on whiff after crossing over the opponent; Forced Knockdown state while airborne; Frame Advantage on Hit or Block varies greatly depending on the angle, spacing and height from ground (higher advantage the closer to the ground C. Viper is when the move connects); Advantage on instant air (Tiger Knee) version at close range: KD +38 / -4 oB (regular jump) | KD +41 / -2 oB (Super Jump)',44,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4b7a4173-cdd8-4219-be28-f940db38248b','C.Viper','OD Burning Kick (air)','','236KK (air)','special',18,7,13,-1,NULL,1000,'H','','Can be input during neutral or forward jump (activates after 7 airborne frames at the earliest); Maintains significant air momentum during forward jump; Performs an alternate version out of High Jump (1F less blockstun but can after only 3 airborne frames for better advantage); Can hit cross-up; +8F extra landing recovery (21F) on whiff after crossing over the opponent; Forced Knockdown state while airborne; Frame Advantage on Hit or Block varies greatly depending on the angle, spacing and height from ground (higher advantage the closer to the ground C. Viper is when the move connects); Advantage on instant air (Tiger Knee) version at close range: KD +37 / +2 oB (regular jump) | KD +41 / +4 oB (Super Jump)',45,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e8daa8fa-d0e4-45ef-b2a1-5ee250311435','C.Viper','Seismic Hammer','','623P','special',24,8,26,-10,NULL,700,'L','sj, su3','1-hit projectile; Distance varies based on button strength: LP close | MP ~50% screen | HP ~80% screen (all versions stop at the corner); Puts opponents into a limited juggle state; Can be feint canceled by pressing or holding K after 11F (total feint duration of 27F) allowing it to bait jumps or anti-projectile Supers; Super Jump cancelable on hit/block only; Combos from Crouch HP (meterless) or Stand HP / Stand HK (Super Jump cancel); Great tool for Burnout pressure especially during SA1 install (can repeatedly chain into itself with Super Jump cancels); Chained HP Seismo can connect 9 times consecutively on a cornered opponent before being pushed out of range (only 7-8 if canceled into from a heavy normal); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Hitbox is low to the ground, allowing opponent to block when landing from an empty jump',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d4a9185e-30fc-41f5-8f52-4eff3531062a','C.Viper','OD Seismic Hammer','','623PP','special',19,8,26,-8,NULL,900,'L','sj, su2, su3','1-hit OD projectile; Covers a wide distance in front of C. Viper (~50% screen); Puts opponents into a limited juggle state; Cannot be feint canceled; Super Jump cancelable on hit/block only; Important combo extension from Crouch MP; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Hitbox is low to the ground, allowing opponent to block when landing from an empty jump',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6d1ee5a0-4f5b-4ddc-b7a1-229a053e11b7','C.Viper','Focus Force (lvl 1)','','214K (lvl 1)','special',23,4,36,-16,NULL,1000,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frames 6-13 or until release; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 14 at the earliest (may be blocked if a light normal is absorbed early in the armor frames); Cancelable into forward dash on frames 12-14 or until button is released (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); Slightly increased oki on Punish Counter; Button can be held to extend the armor and dash cancel frames (up to frame 59) and changing various properties of the move (see the lvl 2 / lvl 3 versions of this move for more details); Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); Focus + Dash cancel can be a useful way to deal with projectiles at some ranges when the Drive gauge is too low to parry; Useful tool against Drive Impact while in Burnout (though the armor starts too late to work in most DI cancel blockstrings); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',48,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('dc7aa917-d8e1-4c74-b585-20933d0764b5','C.Viper','Focus Force (lvl 2)','','214K (lvl 2)','special',30,4,36,-16,NULL,1200,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frame 6 until release; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 14 at the earliest; Cancelable into forward dash on frame 12 until button is released (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); The button must be held for at least 20 frames (up to 58 frames) to execute this partially held (lvl 2) version; Crumples the opponent on Punish Counter (airborne state, +8 before opponent falls to the ground); Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',49,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('0bff6c54-4495-427a-a891-ac5a2a0c47ad','C.Viper','Focus Force (lvl 3)','','214K (lvl 3)','special',69,4,36,-10,NULL,1400,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frames 6-59; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 14 at the earliest; Cancelable into forward dash on frames 12-60 (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); The button must be held for at least 59 frames to execute this fully held (lvl 3) version; Crumples the opponent on hit (airborne state, +25 before opponent falls to the ground); Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',50,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('62611a0d-248d-43f2-8b73-67a1a60e6411','C.Viper','OD Focus Force (lvl 1)','','214KK (lvl 1)','special',20,4,36,-16,NULL,1500,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frames 3-10 or until release; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 11 at the earliest (may be blocked if a light normal is absorbed early in the armor frames); Cancelable into forward dash on frames 9-11 or until buttons are released (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); Slightly increased oki on Punish Counter; Buttons can be held to extend the armor and dash cancel frames (up to frame 57) and changing various properties of the move (see the lvl 2 / lvl 3 versions of this move for more details); Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',51,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ccb5dc62-7331-4f36-8a09-9413f3d1564d','C.Viper','OD Focus Force (lvl 2)','','214KK (lvl 2)','special',30,4,36,-16,NULL,1700,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frame 3 until release; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 11 at the earliest; Cancelable into forward dash on frame 9 until buttons are released (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); The button must be held for at least 20 frames (up to 56 frames) to execute this partially held (lvl 2) version; Crumples the opponent on Punish Counter (airborne state, +8 before opponent falls to the ground); Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',52,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6b614de2-242f-4547-b7e3-48ddf9317390','C.Viper','OD Focus Force (lvl 3)','','214KK (lvl 3)','special',67,4,36,-10,NULL,2000,'H','','Has 1 hit of armor on frames 3-57; Absorbing a strike results in an automatic 10F counter-attack that comes out on frame 11 at the earliest; Cancelable into forward dash on frames 9-58 (cannot dash after absorbing a strike); C. Viper is in a Punish Counter state for the entire duration (including a forward dash cancel); The button must be held for at least 57 frames to execute this fully held (lvl 3) version; Crumples the opponent on hit (airborne state, +25 before opponent falls to the ground); Very powerful stun combo starter; Only the first hit gains extra damage on Punish Counter; Only the second hit causes a Knockdown (can sometimes trade on the first hit, which can result in a follow-up combo for C. Viper); -17 on Punish Counter if only the first hit reaches the opponent (e.g. absorbing a ranged Dhalsim poke)',53,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('777e9d5e-ad0e-46b3-bfd6-bc705d00fc50','C.Viper','Feint','','5K','normal',NULL,NULL,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','This feint can be canceled into during the start-up of Thunder Dash (214P) or Seismic Hammer (623P); The feint itself has a duration of 12F (Thunder Dash) or 16F (Seismic Hammer), but the Feint cancel window on each aforementioned Special is slightly different, resulting in different total duration for the Feint; Total feint duration: LP Thunder Dash 24F (12+12) / MP Thunder Dash 20F (8+12) / HP Thunder Dash 18F (6+12) / Seismic Hammer 27F (11+16); C. Viper is in a counter-hit state for the entire feint duration; The K button can be held to automatically feint at the earliest possible timing (can result in accidental Focus Force activation when performed from a Super Jump cancel even without negative edge enabled)',54,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f6a8feeb-8d36-47ab-9dfc-8506fc60e0f4','C.Viper','High Jump','','1/2/3 > 8/9','normal',6,NULL,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','sp, su','Cancelable into from any grounded normals (except Sweep, Overhead, and f+HK) and Seismic Hammer (623P) on Hit / Block (this cancel is notated by ''sj'' (Super Jump) in the cancel data section of other moves); Jumps slightly higher and ~50% farther than normal jump; The start-up of the jump itself is cancelable into any Special or Super during pre-jump frames 2-6 (2F pre-jump > follow-ups); Airborne on frames 7-46 (Forced Knockdown state); Counter-hit state for entire duration including prejump and landing recovery; Has 3 landing recovery frames like a standard jump; Can only be performed as a Forward or Neutral jump (canceling into Super Jump with an Up+Back input results in a vertical Super Jump); Costs 1 bar of Drive Gauge to perform (but is free of cost during the Limit Decoupler (SA1) install); This High Jump functions like OD Specials, momentarily freezing the Drive Gauge''s passive build-up, but still allowing C. Viper to build back some of the Drive Gauge she just spent on the follow-up hits; Because the pre-jump frames 2-6 are Special cancelable, it means C. Viper can effectively make all her normals (except Sweep, Overhead, and f+HK) Special cancelable (even when they''re not Special cancelable normals); The upwards direction has to be input no later than 8F after any downwards direction in order to execute this Super Jump; Can perform safe jump setups with High Jump (requires KD Advantage of +45); BUG?: Burn Kicks (grounded or airborne) cannot be easily buffered into like all the other Specials performed from a Super Jump Cancel, but rather the Kick input has to be delayed until after the Super Jump script starts, and the Grounded Burn Kick versions can only be executed if the Kick is input on frames 2-3 of the pre-jump frames (this is a 2F window that''s required for many of C. Viper''s optimal damage conversions - For some reason, there is no button buffer accepted on frame 1 of the Super Jump script)',55,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8d96c6d4-6dd9-4e3e-93d2-4fcd73057034','C.Viper','Limit Decoupler','','236236K','super',8,4,22,-34,NULL,2000,'H','','Strike and Throw invincible on frames 1-11 and further invincible to airborne strikes on frames 12-20; Armor Break; Depletes 0.5 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; Temporarily grants C. Viper the ability to use any of her 1-bar moves (High Jump, Tracer Combination, Knuckled Pursuit, or Double Burn) at no cost to the Drive Gauge (doing this while in Burnout allows C. Viper only a single free move usage, which then ends the install timer); Install has a timed duration of 700 frames (~11.7 seconds) which freezes during any hitstop or cinematics; The install becomes active on frame 21 (after active frames) on hit, block, or whiff; C. Viper does not build any Super meter while this install is active (it might even be smart to save up to two levels of Super before activating this install, in order to be able to do another SA1 before the install timer ends to extend the overall install duration); If the first hit trades with a projectile at close range, it''s possible for C. Viper to pick up a limited juggle like HP Thunder Dash, or Level 1/2 Super (depends on spacing / pushback / projectile hitstun)',56,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('439e6fbe-3442-47c4-a657-ea02bf36a3e0','C.Viper','Mission Complete','','214214P','super',7,4,45,-29,NULL,3000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-10; Armor Break; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; C. Viper''s fastest start-up fully invincible Reversal option (cannot be avoided via meaty jabs by the opponent); The opponent is carried over half screen during the cinematic on hit',57,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('87ae5d84-a33b-4214-b12c-2fdb13e53a97','C.Viper','Hard Luck Rejector','','214214K','super',10,4,54,-38,NULL,4000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-13; Armor Break; Depletes 1.5 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~2 Drive Bars for C. Viper; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials',58,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('82253619-f63f-4279-85d6-62ac1d7a0cf7','C.Viper','Hard Luck Rejector (Critical Art)','','214214K (CA)','super',10,4,54,-38,NULL,4500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-13; Armor Break; Critical Art does +500 extra damage over regular version; Depletes 2 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~2.2 Drive Bars for C. Viper; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials',59,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
