('7e59e74a-f7f9-4d23-969c-1094ab78e01f','Ed','OD Psycho Blitz','','214PP','special',13,1,20,-4,NULL,1400,'H','su2, su3','9 hits (7 hits on block/whiff); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on the final 9th hit (the first 8 hits keep the opponent grounded and maintain the current juggle state on airborne opponents); Can be canceled into SA2/SA3 on the last 2 hits (Ed gets different SA2 combo routes depending on which hit is canceled from); All 4-frame normals can punish this move on block, and can interrupt its startup when canceled from Ed''s light normals',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a233109b-b898-4d71-960c-bd5a1f9e51bd','Ed','LK Psycho Flicker','','236LK','special',11,4,26,-6,1,800,'H','su3','1-hit Projectile hitbox; LK has to be held for at least 26 frames to access the enhanced (hold) version; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit; Puts the opponent into a free juggle crumple state on Punish Counter (can be followed up with a Drive Rush combo; +22 frames before opponent is knocked down); Has -2F less recovery frames (24F) on HIT only; Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames); Perfect Parry causes a screen freeze unlike most projectiles; Cancelable into Kill Rush Forward/Back on frame 32 on HIT only (unsafe on hit/counter-hit but grants meterless juggles on Punish Counter)',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4924eac5-d87b-4fc3-b110-7fbeabf58b7f','Ed','LK Psycho Flicker (hold)','','236LK (hold)','special',26,5,24,4,NULL,1000,'H','su3','2-hit Projectile hitbox; Can pierce through 1-hit projectile and grab the opponent (trades with 2-hit projectiles); Pulls the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (Juggle Start is higher (JS3) on airborne opponents); Pulls the opponent towards Ed on block (+4 on block for pressure); The charge animation is cancelable into the Kill Rush command dash (Forward or Back) on frames 16-115; Can be held up to 115 frames at which point the follow-up Flicker automatically executes (120F total start-up); Good oki tool since it allows Ed to continue pressure while also piercing through Supers that are not fully invincible; Recovery frames listed refers to the version that plays out on whiff (Ed only performs the follow-up pull on hit and block); Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames); Parry reduces the distance that Flicker pulls the opponent in, alleviating some of the pressure / mixups that Ed would otherwise get on block; Perfect Parry causes a screen freeze unlike most projectiles, and prevents the opponent from being pulled in',48,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6b4a5abb-3d85-4a9f-88f4-156122122da9','Ed','MK Psycho Flicker','','236MK','special',15,4,26,-6,3,900,'H','su3','1-hit Projectile hitbox; MK has to be held for at least 30 frames to access the enhanced (hold) version; Puts aiborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit; Knocks down the opponent on Counter-Hit (+36 KD); Puts the opponent into a free juggle crumple state on Punish Counter (can be followed up with a Drive Rush combo; +23 frames before opponent is knocked down); Has -1F less recovery frames (25F) on HIT only; Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames); Perfect Parry causes a screen freeze unlike most projectiles; Cancelable into Kill Rush Forward/Back on frame 38 on HIT only (unsafe on hit, but grants better oki on counter-hit or a meterless juggle on Punish Counter)',49,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('45e3213b-be6a-43a5-b001-7d06f79b9211','Ed','MK Psycho Flicker (hold)','','236MK (hold)','special',30,5,24,4,NULL,1000,'H','su3','2-hit Projectile hitbox; Can pierce through 1-hit projectile and grab the opponent (trades with 2-hit projectiles); Pulls the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (Juggle Start is higher (JS3) on airborne opponents); Pulls the opponent towards Ed on block (+4 on block for pressure); The charge animation is cancelable into the Kill Rush command dash (Forward or Back) on frames 16-115; Can be held up to 115 frames at which point the follow-up Flicker automatically executes (120F total start-up); Good oki tool since it allows Ed to continue pressure while also piercing through Supers that are not fully invincible; Recovery frames listed refers to the version that plays out on whiff (Ed only performs the follow-up pull on hit and block); Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames); Parry reduces the distance that Flicker pulls the opponent in, alleviating some of the pressure / mixups that Ed would otherwise get on block; Perfect Parry causes a screen freeze unlike most projectiles, and prevents the opponent from being pulled in',50,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('79d8c51d-52ea-4f05-bdeb-2574bee153d0','Ed','HK Psycho Flicker','','236HK','special',12,8,18,NULL,NULL,800,'H','su3','1-hit Projectile hitbox; Cannot hit grounded opponents (mostly an anti-air / juggle tool); HK has to be held for at least 30 frames to access the enhanced (hold) version; Recovery frames listed refers to the version that plays out on whiff; Puts opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Knockdown Advantage varies greatly depending on how high it connects to the opponent (the higher it hits the higher the KDA is); Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames); Cancelable into Kill Rush Forward/Back after 15F recovery on hit only (grants better midscreen oki or corner juggles)',51,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b202738b-fa00-4fed-ae5d-9ca75cb41c38','Ed','HK Psycho Flicker (hold)','','236HK (hold)','special',30,10,19,NULL,NULL,1000,'H','su3','2-hit Projectile hitbox; Cannot hit grounded opponents (mostly an anti-air / juggle tool); Pulls the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (Juggle Start is higher (JS3) on airborne opponents); The charge animation is cancelable into the Kill Rush command dash (Forward or Back) on frames 16-115; Can be held up to 115 frames at which point the follow-up Flicker automatically executes (120F total start-up); Recovery frames listed refers to the version that plays out on whiff (Ed only performs the follow-up pull on hit); Knockdown Advantage varies greatly depending on how high it connects to the opponent (the higher it hits the higher the KDA is); Extends a forward hurtbox for the entire move duration (this hurtbox is projectile invincible until the active frames)',52,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ac04c166-1d9f-4e54-8c2d-82735b999874','Ed','OD Psycho Flicker','','236KK','special',25,4,32,4,NULL,800,'H','su2, su3','1-hit OD projectile hitbox; Cannot pierce through an OD projectile and grab the opponent (like the non-OD versions can); Pulls the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (Juggle Start is higher (JS3) on airborne opponents); Deals 400 extra damage (1200 total) on airborne opponents; Pulls the opponent towards Ed on block (+4 on block for pressure); Good oki tool since it allows Ed to continue pressure while also piercing through Supers that are not fully invincible; Recovery frames listed refers to the version that plays out on whiff (Ed only performs the follow-up pull on hit and block); Parry reduces the distance that Flicker pulls the opponent in, alleviating some of the pressure / mixups that Ed would otherwise get on block; Perfect Parry causes a screen freeze unlike most projectiles, and prevents the opponent from being pulled in',53,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('15165474-caca-4c8b-ab84-8291aae512cc','Ed','Kill Rush (Forward)','','5KK or 6KK / 66 (cancel)','special',11,NULL,31,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','No head hurtbox on frames 3-26; Cancelable into Kill Switch Break (f+P early) on frames 11-12; Cancelable into Kill Switch Chaser (f+P later) on frames 13-24; Cancelable into during start-up of Psycho Knuckle (hold HP) and Psycho Flicker (hold QCF+K); Counter-hit state for the entire duration',54,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4b0efaee-7543-4e2c-ba22-721ed0f40e92','Ed','Kill Rush > Kill Switch Break','','KK or 6KK / 66 (cancel) > 6P (early)','special',11,3,20,-4,NULL,600,'H','su3','f+P must be input early (frames 1-11 of Kill Rush dash); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Ed); Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',55,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('fc066bb2-a5ae-4107-b8ed-779bb852d640','Ed','Kill Rush > Kill Switch Chaser','','KK or 6KK / 66 (cancel) > 6P (late)','special',13,3,20,-6,NULL,600,'H','su3','f+P must be input late (frames 13-24 of Kill Rush dash); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Ed); Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (sometimes results in better juggle opportunities than Kill Switch Break)',56,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e1671599-d43d-4d89-a865-626bbd86c1ca','Ed','Kill Rush (Backward)','','4KK / 44 (cancel)','special',NULL,NULL,31,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','No head hurtbox on frames 1-10; Cancelable into during start-up of Psycho Flicker (hold QCF+K); Steps back much further than Ed''s regular backdash, albeit with 8F longer total recovery (31F instead of 23F); Counter-hit state for the entire duration; Ed extends a wide forward hurtbox during recovery, making him much more vulnerable to counterattacks (Drive Impact is a guaranteed punish at most ranges when Flicker is canceled from a normal)',57,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('447de284-a3b2-45a4-a211-5dfde4c09efc','Ed','Psycho Storm','','236236K','super',13,2,56,-32,NULL,2000,'H','','Strike and Throw invincible on frames 1-14; Armor Break; Depletes 0.5 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; KDA varies when hitting airborne opponents (slightly higher KDA)',58,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('382bbda0-90bd-4976-a5c0-22dc4cbc5263','Ed','Psycho Cannon','','214214P','super',8,NULL,27,65,NULL,1100,'H','','No invincibility whatsoever; 7-hit Super Projectile; Projectile speed varies depending on button strength (Classic) / direction held (Modern); LP (Classic) / Hold Back (Modern): 0.03 speed; MP (Classic) / Neutral (Modern): 0.045 speed; HP (Classic) / Hold Forward (Modern): 0.09 speed; Last hit launches opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (all the prior hits do not increase the juggle state); If another attack hits the opponent on the same frame as the last hit of this Super, the opponent stays grounded for combo extensions; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; The LP version depletes all Drive Bar on the last hit only (allows the opponent to resume Drive gauge regeneration during Ed''s long juggle sequences); Fantastic tool for combos / pressure / setups; Doesn''t deal a lot of damage by itself but when combined with all of Ed''s other tools this a very powerful Super; 20% penalty to Super meter gain on any of the follow-up hits Ed combos into after this move (but he still has combo routes to build almost a whole Super back); KDA varies greatly depending on a lot of factors (the higher in the air this hits the higher the KDA)',59,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a2d3cf48-6245-43ea-a511-49832732c1dd','Ed','Psycho Chamber','','236236P','super',10,10,64,-49,NULL,4000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-14; Armor Break; Depletes 1.5 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~2.2 Drive Bars for Ed; Can trade on active frames 15-19 (runs out of invincibility) dealing only 500 damage since it doesn''t transition into the cinematic version; Incurs 30% damage scaling when canceled into from qcf+LK/MK Flickers',60,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('66bed832-7d08-4520-8b81-c0cea82d465f','Ed','Psycho Chamber (Critical Art)','','236236P (CA)','super',10,10,64,-49,NULL,4500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-14; Armor Break; Critical Art does +500 extra damage over regular version; Depletes 2 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~2.2 Drive Bars for Ed; Can trade on active frames 15-19 (runs out of invincibility) dealing only 500 damage since it doesn''t transition into the cinematic version',61,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('87e4a0d6-68f4-4351-a336-3cfa8f973be9','Elena','Stand LP','','5LP','normal',5,4,8,-2,4,300,'H','sp, su','Fantastic range for a jab; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',1,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('67c25859-2785-46a2-8c14-3bb6d4e3081b','Elena','Stand MP','','5MP','normal',8,5,15,-3,3,600,'H','su, tc','Great poke / buffer / footsies tool in neutral with a hit confirmable Target Combo follow-up; Active frames 1-2 have shorter range; Active frames 3-5 gain an extended foot hitbox resulting in 2F better advantage on hit or block; Foot hitbox on active frames 3-5 cannot hit crouching opponents or cross-up (behind Elena); The initial leg hitbox that can hit crouching opponents is only active during the first 3 active frames (disappears on active frame 4-5), making it less useful as a meaty; Forces stand on Punish Counter (this enables the MP Target Combo follow-up to combo even on initially crouching opponents); Combos into a variety of follow-ups (5MP / 2MP / 2MK) when used to Punish moves in the midrange; Hit confirmable into Super or the Target Combo extension (too delayed Target Combo cancels only combo with a Counter-hit, Punish Counter, or Drive Rush starter); Hatson''s 2nd favorite move in the game',2,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('55db6b9a-b643-464d-94b3-957127250f0d','Elena','Stand HP','','5HP','normal',12,4,20,-2,2,800,'H','tc','Forces stand on hit; Further range foot hitbox cannot hit crouching opponents (shorter overall range against crouching opponents); Strong horizontal anti-air; Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Hit confirmable (19F) into the HP target combo; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on Punish Counter; The brief extended leg hurtbox on frame 11 of start-up (1F before active) is strike invincible (cannot counter-poke projectiles)',3,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8cf7e13a-413f-406e-8883-0f06b5dbca99','Elena','Stand LK','','5LK','normal',5,3,11,-4,2,300,'H','sp, su','Amazing range for a light normal (furthest of Elena''s light normals) but doesn''t combo into LK Spin Scythe like her jabs do; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',4,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7e289bb7-ebdd-4a99-9176-0568c19f7c5e','Elena','Stand MK','','5MK','normal',6,4,13,1,5,500,'H','sp, su, tc','Core combo and frametrap tool; +2 extra recovery frames (15F) on whiff only',5,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8f8a8db3-f035-460a-8eff-25a57c77b356','Elena','Stand HK','','5HK','normal',12,4,19,-4,2,900,'H','','Crushes low attacks on frames 9-17; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on Punish Counter; The brief extended leg hurtbox on frame 11 of start-up (1F before active) is strike invincible (cannot counter-poke projectiles)',6,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1b3aeb94-51ca-4f75-838f-2215239192c9','Elena','Crouch LP','','2LP','normal',4,3,8,-1,5,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Chains into crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-6 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',7,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d9c0fede-c9fb-46ac-af3a-c5540ae62bf2','Elena','Crouch MP','','2MP','normal',8,3,20,-4,1,600,'H','sp, su','Combo / Poke / Buffer tool with good range; Not an ideal anti-air despite looking like one',8,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('69386d19-ac2a-4fb1-b97e-783f6cea4f49','Elena','Crouch HP','','2HP','normal',9,3,20,-7,6,800,'H','sp, su','Upper body (legs) are invincible to airborne strikes on frames 8-19; Core combo and anti-air tool; Forces stand on hit (important for Rhino Horn combo routes); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Either hit causes an air reset when used as an anti-air (results in very little frame advantage if the first hit connects); Special / Drive Rush cancel occurs on the second hit (even if this hit whiffs); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits',9,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d32c2ffe-020f-4de5-8ae8-6978873a496c','Elena','Crouch LK','','2LK','normal',5,3,8,-1,3,200,'L','ch','Chains into crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',10,datetime('now'),datetime('now'));
