('3b7a7c02-cbe2-4fb3-ac31-8863bfbb2a59','Elena','Crouch MK','','2MK','normal',9,3,16,-4,4,600,'L','tc','+2 extra recovery frames (18F) on whiff or block; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Links into crouch LP, but is always punishable by the opponent''s 4F normal at this range',11,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ca0a9876-ecbd-4a6a-9baa-b9449b0e8cae','Elena','Crouch HK','','2HK','normal',11,3,24,-12,NULL,900,'L','','Has some Juggle potential naturally without Drive Rush; Great range for a sweep but punishable by most other sweeps at max range',12,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('71a557b7-f951-41da-b045-62aacda99170','Elena','Jump LP','','8LP','normal',5,6,NULL,1,5,300,'M','tc','Cross-up that can gain extra frame advantage with a Target Combo extension; Can be used as a fuzzy instant Overhead (except against Blanka) after a deep jump-in Heavy (or jump-in Mediums in Burnout as well)',13,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2005779c-cb1d-45fb-b3db-76c7b791cacb','Elena','Jump MP','','8MP','normal',8,5,NULL,5,11,700,'M','tc','Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Can follow up with a Target Combo extension for an even stronger juggle; Whiffs completely on normal-sized crouching opponents; Shifts the normal jumping hurtbox upward during start-up (helps with avoiding some attacks)',14,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('485a050a-32b5-441e-bdc9-b2b16b9e48c1','Elena','Jump HP','','8HP','normal',10,7,NULL,5,9,800,'M','','Elena''s strongest general purpose jump-in (reaches grounded opponents faster and deals all its damage in one hit unlike jump HK',15,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('fef0d613-7b07-4b90-a77c-8a8c5b71419e','Elena','Jump LK','','8LK','normal',5,6,NULL,-2,2,300,'M','','Strong hitbox priority (especially vertically downwards) that can beat or trade with many anti-air normals; Can be used as a fuzzy instant Overhead after a deep jump-in Heavy (or jump-in Mediums in Burnout as well)',16,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('69dcaad3-6357-4c3f-be76-0586d5dd3a5a','Elena','Jump MK','','8MK','normal',7,5,NULL,5,9,500,'M','','Cross-up; Has a wide hitbox in both directions',17,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1ccba018-b234-41da-9cdd-d918f0ba6bcf','Elena','Jump HK','','8HK','normal',10,2,NULL,7,11,800,'M','','First hit puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Second hit causes a spiked knockdown on airborne opponents; Second hit has the furthest horizontal range on Elena''s jump-ins; Overall weaker as a jump-in since only one hit will connect at most jump timings',18,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('02fa9b0c-f7b3-4c17-8bfd-f48ca1a91c97','Elena','Trunk Slap 1','','6HP','normal',16,4,20,-4,1,900,'H','tc','Mid-range poke tool with high pushback that''s mostly at safe on block (except at close range against exceptionally far-reaching 4F normals) and deals a good amount of drive gauge damage on block; Easily hit confirmable into the Target Combo follow-up (21F hit confirm window)',19,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('471cc137-f2af-4747-9bf5-952ab01e5451','Elena','Handstand Whip 1','','6MK','normal',20,3,19,-2,2,600,'M','tc','Overhead with fast start-up and decent range; Can be hit confirmed into the Target Combo follow-up (17F hit confirm window)',20,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4909e557-b333-4545-aad1-9206c5779c21','Elena','Round Arch','','4HK','normal',14,4,17,-3,3,900,'H','','Crushes low attacks on frames 9-17 and shifts Elena''s throw hurtbox backward starting on frame 5; Not actually airborne despite the animation; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on Punish Counter that can only juggle into LK / MK / OD Scratch Wheel in the corner; +2 extra recovery frames (19F) on whiff only; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',21,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d755ef59-0d24-45ac-b1e9-b2b2cd7fa1bb','Elena','Slide','','3HK','normal',14,9,18,-10,NULL,900,'L','','Crouching state for the entire duration of the move (can slide under attacks that don''t hit Crouch) but does not low profile under fireballs; Half-screen slide that hits low; +4 extra recovery frames (22F) on whiff only',22,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('67f71b32-5509-4307-8aaa-add61e3a7414','Elena','Starling Beak','','5MP > MP','normal',17,5,20,-10,-4,1000,'H','sp, su','Second hit is fully cancelable while the first hit is only Super cancelable; Second hit cannot hit crouching opponents; Frame advantage shown in parenthesis refers to when the second hit whiffs on a crouching opponent; Interruptible 6F gap on block between hits',23,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6d1c73e1-23a8-4e88-971d-55ca267f985f','Elena','Turning Tail','','5HP > HP','normal',17,4,17,-3,NULL,1600,'H','','Both the follow-up hits on HP cannot hit crouching opponents; How unsafe the move is on block varies depending on if the opponent stand or crouch blocks the initial stand HP; Stand block: -3 | Crouch Block after blocking the initial HP standing: -10 | Crouch blocking the initial HP and the follow-up hits: -23; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit with a much stronger juggle after Punish Counter stand HP; Follow-up hits incur 20% damage scaling penatly if used as the first hit of a combo (only occurs if you crouch block the initial HP and then get hit standing)',24,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cf9fb5f6-8c3d-4a75-ba5f-246401bfb457','Elena','Hind Kick','','5MK > HK','normal',12,3,24,-8,NULL,900,'H','sp, su','Elena''s core target combo conversion on crouching opponents (stand HP and crouch MK target combos both can''t hit crouching opponents); Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',25,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c60296de-6c0d-4ebf-b56b-a2a98f0673d4','Elena','Fluttering Lark','','2MK > HK','normal',15,1,20,-9,4,920,'L*H','sp, su','Second hit is fully cancelable; Second hit cannot hit crouching opponents and will always whiff after blocked crouch MK (block data is only applicable if parried); Frame advantage shown in parenthesis refers to when the second hit whiffs on a crouching opponent; +4 extra recovery frames (24F) on whiff',26,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('29133271-c2bb-4c68-bbe3-3eeb3307f592','Elena','Trunk Slap 2','','6HP > HP','normal',13,3,26,-11,-2,1400,'H','tc','Hit confirmable extension from Elena''s long range f+HP that leads to a knockdown ender on hit; Has no juggle potential on its own (does not juggle after a wall splat)',27,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('69e2df1f-30cc-4151-b2c7-9edfb3b0fcde','Elena','Trunk Slap Final','','6HP > HP > HP','normal',7,3,27,-16,NULL,2000,'H','','Target Combo ender with good corner carry and knockdown advantage; Can lead to auto-timed Lynx Whirl pressure on the opponent''s wakeup',28,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2d2b9c0f-beab-44ac-8a41-0701145bf7d5','Elena','Handstand Whip 2','','6MK > MK','normal',14,3,26,-14,NULL,1200,'M*H','','Hit confirmable Target Combo that grants a meterless knockdown from Elena''s long range overhead',29,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3cb062e1-2e8b-49c5-b476-06e35f4e1085','Elena','Soaring Raid','','8LP > 8MK','normal',6,5,NULL,8,12,800,'M','','Both hits cross-up and grant Elena +12 frame advantage combo follow-ups on hit; If the opponent is crouching, Elena lands before the MK follow-up active frames come out; The MK follow-up does not connect as an air-to-air even in Forced Knockdown scenarios',30,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('11b33ad1-1c53-48d0-9168-ace1794c60f1','Elena','Raptor Range','','8MP > 8HP','normal',12,5,NULL,NULL,NULL,1400,'M','','Both hits put airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Cannot hit a grounded opponent',31,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('26321504-f13d-4c23-b920-76c1ef06b607','Elena','Leg Tackle','','LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter; Has a frame perfect corner throw loop against Zangief (dash + walk 2F); Can Drive Rush with frame perfect timing for a 1-bar corner throw loop against standard characters (slightly more lenient against Marisa / Blanka / E. Honda / Zangief)',32,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cbee0e00-3fe8-493e-b3a8-9a2f65035eb5','Elena','Leg Lift Throw','','4LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter; Cannot get throw oki after a corner side switch (except for a frame perfect Drive Rush + Throw against Zangief); Sets up an auto-timed Drive Rush + stand MK (+12 on hit / +8 on block)',33,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8979cd15-e37f-4b59-9f6d-95c71332fd87','Elena','Drive Impact: Giraffe Neck','','HPHK','unique',26,2,35,-3,NULL,800,'H','','2 hits of armor on frames 1-27; Damages opponents Drive Gauge on Block (1/2 bar) | Hit (1 bar) | Counter-Hit (1.25 bar) | Punish Counter (1.5 bar); Knocks down on hit; Crumples on Punish Counter or after absorbing at least 1 attack during start-up (+21 frames before the crumple state goes airborne, followed by airborne state on frames 22-46 before they are grounded) which counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; If the armor absorbs an attack it slows the overall start-up by 1F (27F total instead of 26F); Pushes the opponent far back on hit or block and causes a wall splat if they hit the wall; Wall Splat on block adds 20% damage penalty on the next hit; Wall splats on hit or during Burnout counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; Wall Splat puts opponent into a special juggle state where the next move juggles them even if it doesn''t normally (similar juggle rules as from Drive Rush); Does not cause wall splat if combo''d into from other moves or unblockable setups (Lock); Puts airborne opponents into a long spinning free juggle state when hit as a Punish Counter; Regular KDA without a Wall Splat: +35 KD; Corner wall splat on HIT: +65 KD | Block: +72 HKD; KDA can vary greatly depending on how high the opponent wall splats (higher KDA the higher they wall splat); Can clash with other Drive Impacts if they collide on the same active frame (start at exactly the same time); Costs 1 bar of Drive Gauge; The scrub killer',34,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a338c249-7909-412f-96e6-11f2870973bd','Elena','Drive Reversal: Boar Charge','','6HPHK','unique',20,3,26,-6,NULL,500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-22 (frames 1-20 when used on wake-up as a Reversal); Armor Break (blows through all armor like Drive Impact); Can be performed during blockstun or from a successful parry (trying to Drive Reversal after the blockstun is over will result in a Drive Impact); Can also be performed during wake-up as a Reversal, doing it this way speeds up the start-up frames by 2 frames (18F start-up instead of 20F); Drive Reversal immediately removes the current blockstun you''re in and starts the attack; Causes a 4F screen freeze that occurs after the 6th start-up frame, which can mess up the opponents input timing, or enable them to do a simple input OS to counter the Drive Reversal; Safe on block (-2) when used against an opponent currently in Burnout; Costs 2 bars of Drive Gauge',35,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('432aa185-f681-4335-9a17-b280b46a6dbe','Elena','Drive Parry','','MPMK','unique',1,12,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Parries all strikes and projectiles (high and low) from frame 1; 12F parry window (can hold the parry to extend the parry window); Perfect Parry occurs on the first 2 active frames (cannot achieve Perfect Parry if you buffer into parry by holding it during Reversal windows; Perfect Parries have to be timed properly); Can still hold charge directions during Parry; Can block during the recovery frames of a regular parry (can still get hit during the recovery frames if you don''t block correctly); Getting thrown or hit at any point during the recovery frames of a whiffed parry attempt results in a Punish Counter; Successfully parrying a move puts you into the same amount of blockstun as that move would regularly do on block (but a Perfect Parry has only 1F of recovery); Throw invincible during the recovery of a successful parry (just like during blockstun); Perfect Parrying a strike has only 1F of recovery and disables the opponent from canceling their attack (basically a guaranteed punish opportunity); After a successful Perfect Parry, you suffer a 50% penalty to your Damage, Drive Gauge Generation, and Drive Gauge Damage on any of your following attacks when punishing the opponent (in addition, both you and the opponent suffer a 20% penalty to their Super Meter gain during this period); Fully invincible for 6F after a successful Perfect Parry against a strike, during which period you can cancel into anything you want and it carries over the brief invincibility frames; Perfect Parrying projectiles puts you into fixed 10 frames of recovery and applies the same 50% scaling penalties (and 20% Super Meter penalty) on your following attacks when punishing the opponent; Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will result in a regular parry for the strike attack (effectively ignoring the projectile''s hitstop / blockstun); Perfect Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will give a screen freeze like you Perfect Parried a Strike, but still give you 10F recovery as if you had Perfect Parried a Projectile; Can cancel into Drive Rush during active frames 3 and onward (fastest Drive Rush method is to buffer a forward input before doing parry + forward again); Can cancel into Drive Reversal from a successful parry (just like you can normally during blockstun); Costs 1/2 bar Drive Gauge (continues to deplete Drive Gauge as you hold the Parry); You lose the parry if you go into Burnout from the Drive Gauge cost; Rewards 1 bar Drive Gauge (1/2 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a strike; Rewards 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge (0 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a projectile; Rewards 2 bars of Drive Gauge (1.5 bars total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successful parrying a Drive Impact; Successfully parrying a strike attack splits the regular block pushback between both players (while Perfect Parrying a strike removes all of its pushback); Successfully parrying a projectile or Drive Impact reduces the pushback of it by half (while Perfect Parrying a projectile or Drive Impact removes all of its pushback); Your hurtbox and throw box expand slightly towards the opponent for the entire duration of the Parry (Throw box extension starts instantly on frame 1, while the Hurtbox extension starts on frame 3, after the initial 2F Perfect Parry window); Parrying while crouching maintains a regular crouch hurtbox for the first 2 frames of the parry (during the initial Perfect Parry window)',36,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c6a9e14e-addb-498d-813a-cf0fee47999d','Elena','Drive Rush','','MPMK / 66 (cancel)','unique',9,45,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Dashes forward and enhances the next normal used out of the Drive Rush with +4 extra hitstun / blockstun (some moves also get unique properties enhanced such as juggle state); The +4 bonus frame advantage gained from a Drive Rush enhanced move also stacks with any bonus frame advantage that move may have gained from Counter-Hit or Punish Counter; Cancelable into from special cancelable grounded normals; Drive Rush maintains buffers (freezes the buffer window) during it start-up and freeze frames - This allows players to do things normally not possible within the normal buffer windows, such as Drive Rushing into a charge special; The initial freeze frames that occur when a Drive Rush happens eats the opponents inputs; Framedata shown in parentheses refers to the Drive Rush version used from a Parry; Drive Rush recovery frames is only 24F total (23F if done from a Parry) - but the enhanced dash itself is 46F total (45F if done from Parry) and you can cancel it as early as frame 9 (frame 11 if done from a Parry); You stop building any form of Drive Gauge on your attacks after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (but you still continue to build drive gauge as normal if you did Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Applies extra damage scaling penalty after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (no damage scaling if you use Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Costs 3 bars of Drive Gauge if canceled into from a move; Costs 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge if canceled into from Parry (for a total of 1 bar of Drive Gauge when you factor in the initial 1/2 bar cost of the Parry)',37,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ec0656e7-09c5-41f9-8630-6d8e35f90642','Elena','Taunt','','5PPPKKK','unique',21,3,120,-106,NULL,300,'H','','Framedata listed is for the down+Taunt version that deals a bit of damage (300) but is very punishable on hit or block; Back Taunt can transition to a handstand walk by holding forward or backward on frames 181-370',38,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ba54bf96-991c-4fbb-848c-b2e5166069a5','Elena','LK Rhino Horn','','236LK','special',13,5,3,-9,NULL,1100,'H','su3','Airborne on frames 13-36 (crushes Low attacks on frames 15-34); Cannot hit crouching (core combo tool in all other situations); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; +3 extra recovery frames (19F) on block and whiff; KDA (Knockdown advantage) listed refers to hitting grounded opponents (KDA is usually slightly less when hitting airborne opponents mid-combo)',39,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('baf566e5-28d3-4eb1-a298-e5e18495bd2b','Elena','MK Rhino Horn','','236MK','special',17,5,3,-9,NULL,1200,'H','su3','Airborne on frames 17-41 (crushes Low attacks on frames 19-39); Cannot hit crouching (core combo tool in all other situations); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; +4 extra recovery frames (20F) on block and whiff; KDA (Knockdown advantage) listed refers to hitting grounded opponents (KDA is usually slightly less when hitting airborne opponents mid-combo)',40,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('59a06317-7733-4e32-9cb9-d008cab47296','Elena','HK Rhino Horn','','236HK','special',21,5,3,-9,NULL,1300,'H','su3','Airborne on frames 21-45 (crushes Low attacks on frames 23-43); Cannot hit crouching (core combo tool in all other situations); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; +4 extra recovery frames (20F) on block and whiff; KDA (Knockdown advantage) listed refers to hitting grounded opponents (KDA is usually slightly less when hitting airborne opponents mid-combo)',41,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('40829865-b21c-4b36-98f9-3dc2fe8812aa','Elena','OD Rhino Horn','','236KK','special',11,7,3,-9,NULL,1200,'H','su2, su3','Airborne on frames 11-38 (crushes Low attacks on frames 13-35); Cannot hit crouching (core combo tool in all other situations); Tends to travel underneath and past airborne opponents a lot (can be used to switch sides mid-combo and still juggle into Scratch Wheel on the other side); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; +6 extra recovery frames (19F) on block and whiff; KDA (Knockdown advantage) listed refers to hitting grounded opponents (KDA is usually slightly less when hitting airborne opponents mid-combo)',42,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('58cd96e1-a642-4a7f-ba23-46c0ff7f5d13','Elena','LK Scratch Wheel','','623LK','special',5,5,25,-24,NULL,1000,'H','','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-9; Airborne on frames 7-34 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Incurs a 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo (like in high hitting anti-air or juggle scenarios)',43,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('121921a0-847f-4114-99ef-8f17679abbbd','Elena','MK Scratch Wheel','','623MK','special',6,3,30,-30,NULL,1200,'H','','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-11; Airborne on frames 7-41 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 600 less damage (600) on active frames 4-6 (first hit whiffs); Incurs a 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo (like in high hitting anti-air or juggle scenarios)',44,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('73f75ae7-b65c-404b-9bba-55afa86dfdf1','Elena','HK Scratch Wheel','','623HK','special',7,2,34,-33,NULL,1400,'H','','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-12; Airborne on frames 7-46 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 500 less damage (900) on active frames 3-4 (first hit whiffs); Deals 900 less damage (500) on active frames 5-6 (first two hits both whiff); Incurs a 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo (like in high hitting anti-air or juggle scenarios)',45,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('982ca67a-e321-4bb2-a17c-8c9363550484','Elena','OD Scratch Wheel','','623KK','special',6,4,24,-46,NULL,1600,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-8; Airborne on frames 7-52 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Elena); Deals 450 less damage (1150) on active frames 5-6 (first hit whiffs); Incurs a 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo (like in high hitting anti-air or juggle scenarios)',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3c34dcce-9747-49a0-a67a-f876a1e90ab6','Elena','LP Lynx Song','','236LP','special',13,NULL,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Projectile invincible on frames 11-21; Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 3-26; Total distance traveled: 1.37; 0.72 is the minimun distance traveled (13 frames) before canceling into f+LK Leopard Snap follow-up; 0.87 is the minimum distance traveled (16 frames) before canceling into all the other follow-ups (f+MK Harvest Circle / f+HK Mallet Smash) including additional rolls (Lynx Whirl); Start-up frames (13/16) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap; f+LK follow-up can be executed 3 frames earlier than all the other follow-ups)',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f468cf55-8f8b-49c0-a524-7e8c82dde56b','Elena','MP Lynx Song','','236MP','special',13,NULL,36,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Projectile invincible on frames 11-22; Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 3-26; Total distance traveled: 1.72; 0.66 is the minimun distance traveled (13 frames) before canceling into f+LK Leopard Snap follow-up; 0.98 is the minimum distance traveled (18 frames) before canceling into all the other follow-ups (f+MK Harvest Circle / f+HK Mallet Smash) including additional rolls (Lynx Whirl); Start-up frames (13/18) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap; f+LK follow-up can be executed 5 frames earlier than all the other follow-ups)',48,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1f7e14f3-cc48-4dee-906d-9113e2b90576','Elena','HP Lynx Song','','236HP','special',16,NULL,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Projectile invincible on frames 11-24; Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 3-26; Total distance traveled: 2.21; 1.08 is the minimun distance traveled (16 frames) before canceling into f+LK Leopard Snap follow-up; 1.35 is the minimum distance traveled (19 frames) before canceling into all the other follow-ups (f+MK Harvest Circle / f+HK Mallet Smash) including additional rolls (Lynx Whirl); Start-up frames (16/19) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap; f+LK follow-up can be executed 3 frames earlier than all the other two follow-ups)',49,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6033dd8c-3dcc-4bf3-9f23-eef82002944c','Elena','OD Lynx Song (Lynx Whirl)','','236PP','special',15,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Gives Elena instant access to the Lynx Whirl (enhanced) follow-ups without requiring a second roll (very useful for combos / pressure / punishing projectiles); Projectile invincible on frames 8-26; Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 3-26; Total distance traveled: 2.02; 0.93 is the minimun distance traveled (15 frames) before canceling into f+LK Leopard Snap follow-up; 1.19 is the minimum distance traveled (18 frames) before canceling into all the other follow-ups (f+MK Harvest Circle / f+HK Mallet Smash) including additional rolls (Lynx Whirl); Start-up frames (15/18) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap; f+LK follow-up can be executed 3 frames earlier than all the other follow-ups)',50,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('575468da-a192-4f14-ba1f-cba1dcc3b5a8','Elena','Lynx Song > Leopard Snap','','236P > 6LK','special',10,5,22,-5,NULL,1000,'H','su3','Combo / Poke / Harassment tool that''s mostly safe on block due to the pushback; Elena loses her Projectile invincibility and Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Song (Roll) immediately when she transitions into this follow-up (the other follow-ups maintain those properties for longer and are thus more suited for countering projectiles); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Minimum start-up varies depending on which version of Lynx Song (Roll) Elena does (LP: 13+10 | MP: 13+10 | HP: 16+10 | OD: 15+10)',51,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3cf022a5-a3c2-4cc0-b74b-1042b672fa2b','Elena','Lynx Song > Harvest Circle','','236P > 6MK','special',8,3,23,-9,NULL,900,'H','','Projectile invincible on frames 1-10 (not factoring in the Projectile invincibility frames from the prior Lynx Song roll); Extended kick hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 8-10 (during the active frames) to help with anti-airing; Combo / Projectile punish / Situational anti-air tool; Elena loses her Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Song (Roll) immediately when she transition into this follow-up; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Minimum start-up varies depending on which version of Lynx Song (Roll) Elena does (LP: 16+8 | MP: 18+8 | HP: 19+8 | OD: 18+8)',52,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e36d3d82-855a-4df7-9c3c-43eb83b54c8e','Elena','Lynx Song > Mallet Smash','','236P > 6HK','special',22,3,19,-3,2,800,'M','','Overhead + Low & Throw Crush tool; Projectile invincible on frames 5-24 (top Head hurtbox section is not Projectile invincible); Airborne on frames 14-23 (Elena counts as Standing on the last active frame) and low crushes on frames 14-24; Elena loses her Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Song (Roll) immediately when she transition into this follow-up (also briefly loses her Projectile invincibility before gaining it again on frame 5 of start-up); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit; Minimum start-up varies depending on which version of Lynx Song (Roll) Elena does (LP: 16+22 | MP: 18+22 | HP: 19+22 | OD: 18+22)',53,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('0d371d33-2a77-4fb3-bdd7-73c7f7922a2c','Elena','Lynx Whirl','','236P / 214K > 6P','special',15,NULL,28,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Accessible from either a prior Lynx Song roll (QCF+P) or Spin Scythe (QCB+K); Projectile invincible on frames 1-21 on the Light version or frames 1-26 on the Medium / Heavy versions (not factoring in the Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Song roll (QCF+P) or Spin Scythe (QCB+K) specials); Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 1-26 (not factoring in the Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Song roll (QCF+P) or Spin Scythe (QCB+K) specials); Total distance traveled on this Whirl follow-up varies depending on which strength is used (Light: 1.43 | Medium: 1.94 | Heavy: 2.46); Start-up frames (15/18/20) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap (LK): frames 15-21 | Harvest Circle (MK): frames 18-21 | Mallet Smash (HK): frames 18-21 | Lynx Whirl (roll again): frames 20-21)',54,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('07060958-70ea-4029-9002-45182117b2cc','Elena','OD Lynx Whirl','','236PP > 6P','special',15,NULL,34,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Accessible from a prior OD Lynx Song roll (QCF+PP); Projectile invincible on frames 1-26 (not factoring in the Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior OD Lynx Song roll (QCF+PP)); Crouch size hurtbox (but still in a Standing state) on frames 1-26 (not factoring in the Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior OD Lynx Song roll (QCF+P)); Total distance traveled: 2.59 (travels even further and faster than the HP version); Start-up frames (15/18/20) refer to the minimum amount of frames that must play out before Elena can execute the follow-ups (Leopard Snap (LK): frames 15-24 | Harvest Circle (MK): frames 18-24 | Mallet Smash (HK): frames 18-24 | Lynx Whirl (roll again): frames 20-24); Largely the same as the non-OD Lynx Whirl versions, except this version has a longer cancel window for the follow-ups',55,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ffe769e0-a371-4899-876b-211b22e22be8','Elena','Lynx Whirl > Leopard Snap','','Whirl > 6LK','special',10,5,14,1,NULL,1200,'H','su3','Combo / Pressure tool that lets Elena continue her pressure even on block (+1); +1 extra recovery frames (15F) on whiff only; Elena loses her Projectile invincibility and Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) immediately when she transitions into this follow-up (the other follow-ups maintain those properties for longer and are thus more suited for countering projectiles); Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (key combo tool in optimal / max damage combos); Can be used after Spin Scythe to continue the pressure on hit (2F gap frametrap on hit)',56,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('53ae9bed-dcca-46a2-a283-f5f0cbc17d56','Elena','Lynx Whirl > Harvest Circle','','Whirl > 6MK','special',8,3,14,-4,NULL,1300,'H','','Projectile invincible on frames 1-10 (not factoring in the Projectile invincibility frames from the prior Lynx Whirl roll); Extended kick hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 8-10 (during the active frames) to help with anti-airing; +2 extra recovery frames (16F) on block and whiff; Combo / Projectile punish / Situational anti-air tool; Elena loses her Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) immediately when she transition into this follow-up; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Combos from Spin Scythe > Whirl cancel on Counter-Hit / Punish Counter; The first hit pulls opponents inward on hit or block (ensures combo consistency as Elena moves backwards)',57,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('12d8cd22-ebe5-46cc-92df-c08be5516090','Elena','Lynx Whirl > Mallet Smash','','Whirl > 6HK','special',22,2,16,3,4,1000,'M','','Overhead + Low & Throw Crush tool; Projectile invincible on frames 5-27 (top Head hurtbox section is not Projectile invincible) - not factoring in the Projectile invincibility frames from the prior Lynx Whirl roll; Low crushes on frames 5-22; Airborne on frames 9-22 (Elena counts as Standing on the second active frame); Can also be used for oki or to continue the pressure even on block (+3); Elena loses her Crouch size hurtboxes from the prior Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) immediately when she transition into this follow-up (also briefly loses her Projectile invincibility before gaining it again on frame 5 of start-up); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit',58,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4b5fc37a-1afc-4bb8-9921-c5607f9be1a5','Elena','LK Spin Scythe','','214LK','special',15,4,24,-12,NULL,900,'H','su3','First 2 hits force stand on hit (so the last 2 hits to also combo); Further range foot hitbox on the first 2 hits cannot hit crouching opponents (shorter overall range against crouching opponents, which can affect whiff punishes); Last 2 hits cannot hit crouching opponents at all; Block disadvantage shown in parenthesis (-35) refers to when the last 2 hits whiff on crouch blocking opponents; Cancelable into Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) from the 2nd hit, allowing Elena to extend her combos or to keep up the pressure / mixup the opponent; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage on the first 2 hits; Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) cancel from the 2nd hit combos into Harvest Combo (f+MK) on Counter-Hit and Leopard Snap (f+LK) on Punish Counter; Last hit puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (first 2 hits keep them grounded)',59,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2d2e5213-41bb-4024-b8f4-6eefa3479f36','Elena','MK Spin Scythe','','214MK','special',20,4,27,-14,NULL,1000,'H','su3','First 2 hits force stand on hit (so the last 2 hits to also combo); Further range foot hitbox on the first 2 hits cannot hit crouching opponents (shorter overall range against crouching opponents, which can affect whiff punishes); Last 2 hits cannot hit crouching opponents at all; Block disadvantage shown in parenthesis (-37) refers to when the last 2 hits whiff on crouch blocking opponents; Cancelable into Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) from the 2nd hit, allowing Elena to extend her combos or to keep up the pressure / mixup the opponent; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage on the first 2 hits; Lynx Whirl (enhanced Roll) cancel from the 2nd hit combos into Harvest Combo (f+MK) on Counter-Hit and Leopard Snap (f+LK) on Punish Counter; Last hit puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (first 2 hits keep them grounded); +42 KD when hitting grounded opponents which sets up for a safe jump if close enough to the corner',60,datetime('now'),datetime('now'));
