('97bbff79-ab47-4b6e-be80-3781cc047b0c','Mai','Stand LP','','5LP','normal',4,3,7,-2,5,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Shorter range than crouch LP but +1F extra hitstun meaning move combo potential (naturally combos into things like LP/MP Ryuuenbu (QCB special); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',1,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('598de3f5-47fe-423c-9cec-5fb6ac0d6bd7','Mai','Stand MP','','5MP','normal',8,4,15,-3,2,600,'H','sp, su, tc','Decent range with strong hitbox priority and fully cancelable makes this a solid neutral tool',2,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cbfdf42f-ea98-4614-a759-3ed9f953b990','Mai','Stand HP','','5HP','normal',9,3,21,-3,1,800,'H','sp, su','Core combo and whiff punish tool that leads into Mai''s highest damage routes',3,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5228e8fc-ad2c-421f-992a-0551c3003309','Mai','Stand LK','','5LK','normal',4,3,8,-1,1,300,'H','sp, su, tc','Very short range but goes into the LK Target Combo follow-ups; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; BUG?: Has 1F extra hitstop compared to the universal rule of light attacks',4,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('30475c68-912f-4ee0-ac7b-bb5721c81848','Mai','Stand MK','','5MK','normal',9,3,18,-4,5,700,'H','','Good combo / poke / whiff punish tool; Mai lifts up her front leg hurtbox on frames 4-17 making this a good tool against low attacks; Good hitbox priority; Can easily be hit confirmed into SA2 on Punish Counter (also works on Counter-Hit at closer ranges)',5,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f094ab00-234d-4f4e-9980-a3c2ec714c0f','Mai','Stand HK','','5HK','normal',14,3,19,-3,3,900,'H','','Good whiff punish tool; Causes a crumple-like free juggle state on a grounded Punish Counter (opponent is airborne for any follow-up hits); Mai lifts up her standing leg hurtbox on frames 10-16 making this a decent tool against low attacks; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on Punish Counter; The brief extended leg hurtbox on frame 13 of start-up (1F before active) is strike invincible (cannot counter-poke projectiles); +3F extra recovery frames (22F) on whiff',6,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('63a70b8b-34ed-41c1-bae1-fe3a6bf47a8d','Mai','Crouch LP','','2LP','normal',4,3,7,-1,4,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Furthest range of Mai''s light buttons (but less combo potential than 5LP due to 1F less hitstun); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-6 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',7,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('da995984-7f18-49db-a3fc-9f7bb2b8dbf6','Mai','Crouch MP','','2MP','normal',6,4,15,-3,5,600,'H','sp, su','Decent combo / buffer tool; Solid range for a crouch MP; +2F extra recovery frames (17F) on whiff',8,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('dd9a7d94-8efd-4ffd-b071-f6de1a6a9ce9','Mai','Crouch HP','','2HP','normal',10,2,19,-3,4,800,'H','','Mostly a combo tool (like from Drive Rush) but the first hit does have very strong hitbox priority for counter-poking; First hit pulls in the opponent on hit or block',9,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cb488880-ba80-4984-aad1-898d03ea524c','Mai','Crouch LK','','2LK','normal',5,3,8,-2,2,200,'L','ch','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',10,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('eb1b2037-9d64-41db-bf2c-299d5f2274ad','Mai','Crouch MK','','2MK','normal',7,3,19,-6,-2,500,'L','sp, su','Your average SF6 crouch MK; Incurs a 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',11,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f1069a70-d419-4b44-a501-30044f61cc01','Mai','Crouch HK','','2HK','normal',9,3,22,-11,NULL,900,'L','','Has good hitbox priority against low attacks (the extended kick hurtbox can effectively low crush some low attacks); +1F extra recovery frames (23F) on block; +3F extra recovery frames (25F) on whiff',12,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('db934f43-7ae2-4992-a18d-a69e5fc98c14','Mai','Jump LP','','8LP','normal',4,9,NULL,3,6,300,'M','','Fast air-to-air option; Best horizontal hitbox priority of Mai''s jumping attacks',13,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cd07ced7-5f9e-4ce7-aac2-28fde6ea828b','Mai','Jump MP','','8MP','normal',7,5,NULL,3,7,600,'M','','Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Good air-to-air hitboxes',14,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e6d7bc32-7f9a-492a-a2d3-60a56f93840b','Mai','Jump HP','','8HP','normal',9,5,NULL,3,7,800,'M','','Good hitbox for vertical air approaches',15,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7c93664f-3dd7-4e1c-81f1-4bfb7aecc34c','Mai','Jump LK','','8LK','normal',5,7,NULL,1,5,300,'M','','Cross-up; Can be used as an instant Overhead',16,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('fe857239-aeb5-493f-832c-1321edda02a6','Mai','Jump MK','','8MK','normal',7,5,NULL,4,8,500,'M','','Cross-up',17,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('9b271ce1-f26f-43da-9737-fc8644696e02','Mai','Jump HK','','8HK','normal',10,6,NULL,7,11,800,'M','','Furthest horizontal range of Mai''s jump-in attacks',18,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3eec6ac0-5239-4126-9c4f-a79edfa72792','Mai','Senkotsu Uchi','','6MP','normal',20,3,18,-3,2,600,'M','','Fast Overhead with decent frame advantage (can meaty on last active frame to get jab combo follow-ups); Causes a spiked knockdown on airborne opponents',19,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2841882b-776f-4ce9-b065-d6c3d03dbc54','Mai','Handstand Kick','','4HK','normal',8,5,20,-1,3,800,'H','','Legs and lower body (keep in mind Mai is upside down) are invincible to airborne strikes on frames 8-12 making this a fantastic anti-air; Forced stand on hit (important for some combo routes); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Mai); Very easily hit confirmable into its Target Combo follow-up; Decent oki tool with lots of active frames that can be up to +7 on hit / +3 on block',20,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4e51a17f-4f8f-4da7-b4c8-3c6118dd5a33','Mai','Hien Ren Kyaku 1','','5LK > 5LK','normal',7,2,20,-10,-2,400,'H','tc','Forces stand on hit; This 2-hit version can be useful for some combo extensions while the latter hits of Kachousen (fan) are falling down onto the opponent',21,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('14762ffb-318f-4262-a555-bb75af59a2bd','Mai','Hien Ren Kyaku 2','','5LK > 5LK > 5LK','normal',10,2,24,-10,3,500,'H','sp, su2','Mai leaps off the opponent and can be followed up with a Musasabi no Mai (Divekick) or SA2 before landing (Divekick can be delayed quite a bit for potentially better angle and + frames on Flame Stock version); Airborne on frames 10-35 (Forced Knockdown state) followed by 4F landing recovery; True blockstring and mostly safe on block midscreen due to the distance it creates; Some Supers reach far enough to punish Mai, but in many cases she can respond with Divekick or Air Level 2 Super on reaction to avoid the punish; Divekick follow-up won''t combo if the Divekick is delayed too much (59F hit confirm window for the Divekick to still combo); Divekick follow-up leads into +42 safe jump oki if the initial LK hits slightly spaced out',22,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2c2a9ce9-d589-4ba1-914e-ff6ed0478606','Mai','Hoshi Kujaku','','4HK > 5HK','normal',9,3,30,-11,NULL,2000,'H','','Extremely easy to hit confirm (28F window); Puts opponents into a limited juggle state (juggle follow-ups depend on if the opponent was grounded or airborne like after a Drive Rush juggle extension); Mai becomes fully invincible after the HK follow-up lands on hit; +8 extra recovery frames on whiff',23,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7ded5461-302a-488d-8ba0-365a4dbf1216','Mai','Shiranui Gourin','','LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Throw Loop: Dash up for +3 mixup between strike / throw (corner only); Throw loop leaves Mai at the perfect spacing to walk backwards to bait the opponent''s throw tech (except vs. Blanka, E. Honda, Marisa, and Zangief); Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',24,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7c606e70-e2f8-4665-beef-e5e0618a33f5','Mai','Fuusha Kuzushi','','4LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Back Throw oki: Can do meaty attacks or Drive Rush into strike / throw (corner only); Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',25,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4c9c31b1-ad63-41fe-a159-a84870abf56c','Mai','Yume Zakura','','LPLK (air)','throw',5,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Corner Air Throw: Dash up for +2 mixup between strike / throw (corner only); Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',26,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('900d27ce-0eb0-41a4-9d4d-75bd798fbb65','Mai','Drive Impact: Botan Ichige','','HPHK','unique',26,2,35,-3,NULL,800,'H','','2 hits of armor on frames 1-27; Damages opponents Drive Gauge on Block (1/2 bar) | Hit (1 bar) | Counter-Hit (1.25 bar) | Punish Counter (1.5 bar); Knocks down on hit; Crumples on Punish Counter or after absorbing at least 1 attack during start-up (+21 frames before the crumple state goes airborne, followed by airborne state on frames 22-46 before they are grounded) which counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; If the armor absorbs an attack it slows the overall start-up by 1F (27F total instead of 26F); Pushes the opponent far back on hit or block and causes a wall splat if they hit the wall; Wall Splat on block adds 20% damage penalty on the next hit; Wall splats on hit or during Burnout counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; Wall Splat puts opponent into a special juggle state where the next move juggles them even if it doesn''t normally (similar juggle rules as from Drive Rush); Does not cause wall splat if combo''d into from other moves or unblockable setups (Lock); Puts airborne opponents into a long spinning free juggle state when hit as a Punish Counter; Regular KDA without a Wall Splat: +35 KD; Corner wall splat on HIT: +65 KD | Block: +72 HKD; KDA can vary greatly depending on how high the opponent wall splats (higher KDA the higher they wall splat); Can clash with other Drive Impacts if they collide on the same active frame (start at exactly the same time); Costs 1 bar of Drive Gauge; The scrub killer',27,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c52471d3-92ea-4d59-a7fc-66654c3f5f67','Mai','Drive Reversal: Yusura Ume','','6HPHK','unique',20,3,26,-6,NULL,500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-22 (frames 1-20 when used on wake-up as a Reversal); Armor Break (blows through all armor like Drive Impact); Can be performed during blockstun or from a successful parry (trying to Drive Reversal after the blockstun is over will result in a Drive Impact); Can also be performed during wake-up as a Reversal, doing it this way speeds up the start-up frames by 2 frames (18F start-up instead of 20F); Drive Reversal immediately removes the current blockstun you''re in and starts the attack; Causes a 4F screen freeze that occurs after the 6th start-up frame, which can mess up the opponents input timing, or enable them to do a simple input OS to counter the Drive Reversal; Safe on block (-2) when used against an opponent currently in Burnout; Costs 2 bars of Drive Gauge',28,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c6e64f0e-75e2-4878-a15b-a13cf43d5aae','Mai','Drive Parry','','MPMK','unique',1,12,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Parries all strikes and projectiles (high and low) from frame 1; 12F parry window (can hold the parry to extend the parry window); Perfect Parry occurs on the first 2 active frames (cannot achieve Perfect Parry if you buffer into parry by holding it during Reversal windows; Perfect Parries have to be timed properly); Can still hold charge directions during Parry; Can block during the recovery frames of a regular parry (can still get hit during the recovery frames if you don''t block correctly); Getting thrown or hit at any point during the recovery frames of a whiffed parry attempt results in a Punish Counter; Successfully parrying a move puts you into the same amount of blockstun as that move would regularly do on block (but a Perfect Parry has only 1F of recovery); Throw invincible during the recovery of a successful parry (just like during blockstun); Perfect Parrying a strike has only 1F of recovery and disables the opponent from canceling their attack (basically a guaranteed punish opportunity); After a successful Perfect Parry, you suffer a 50% penalty to your Damage, Drive Gauge Generation, and Drive Gauge Damage on any of your following attacks when punishing the opponent (in addition, both you and the opponent suffer a 20% penalty to their Super Meter gain during this period); Fully invincible for 6F after a successful Perfect Parry against a strike, during which period you can cancel into anything you want and it carries over the brief invincibility frames; Perfect Parrying projectiles puts you into fixed 10 frames of recovery and applies the same 50% scaling penalties (and 20% Super Meter penalty) on your following attacks when punishing the opponent; Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will result in a regular parry for the strike attack (effectively ignoring the projectile''s hitstop / blockstun); Perfect Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will give a screen freeze like you Perfect Parried a Strike, but still give you 10F recovery as if you had Perfect Parried a Projectile; Can cancel into Drive Rush during active frames 3 and onward (fastest Drive Rush method is to buffer a forward input before doing parry + forward again); Can cancel into Drive Reversal from a successful parry (just like you can normally during blockstun); Costs 1/2 bar Drive Gauge (continues to deplete Drive Gauge as you hold the Parry); You lose the parry if you go into Burnout from the Drive Gauge cost; Rewards 1 bar Drive Gauge (1/2 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a strike; Rewards 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge (0 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a projectile; Rewards 2 bars of Drive Gauge (1.5 bars total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successful parrying a Drive Impact; Successfully parrying a strike attack splits the regular block pushback between both players (while Perfect Parrying a strike removes all of its pushback); Successfully parrying a projectile or Drive Impact reduces the pushback of it by half (while Perfect Parrying a projectile or Drive Impact removes all of its pushback); Your hurtbox and throw box expand slightly towards the opponent for the entire duration of the Parry (Throw box extension starts instantly on frame 1, while the Hurtbox extension starts on frame 3, after the initial 2F Perfect Parry window); Parrying while crouching maintains a regular crouch hurtbox for the first 2 frames of the parry (during the initial Perfect Parry window)',29,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('24f923c2-fa0e-413d-9684-0f897a7ca6ea','Mai','Drive Rush','','MPMK / 66 (cancel)','unique',9,45,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Dashes forward and enhances the next normal used out of the Drive Rush with +4 extra hitstun / blockstun (some moves also get unique properties enhanced such as juggle state); The +4 bonus frame advantage gained from a Drive Rush enhanced move also stacks with any bonus frame advantage that move may have gained from Counter-Hit or Punish Counter; Cancelable into from special cancelable grounded normals; Drive Rush maintains buffers (freezes the buffer window) during it start-up and freeze frames - This allows players to do things normally not possible within the normal buffer windows, such as Drive Rushing into a charge special; The initial freeze frames that occur when a Drive Rush happens eats the opponents inputs; Framedata shown in parentheses refers to the Drive Rush version used from a Parry; Drive Rush recovery frames is only 24F total (23F if done from a Parry) - but the enhanced dash itself is 46F total (45F if done from Parry) and you can cancel it as early as frame 9 (frame 11 if done from a Parry); You stop building any form of Drive Gauge on your attacks after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (but you still continue to build drive gauge as normal if you did Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Applies extra damage scaling penalty after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (no damage scaling if you use Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Costs 3 bars of Drive Gauge if canceled into from a move; Costs 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge if canceled into from Parry (for a total of 1 bar of Drive Gauge when you factor in the initial 1/2 bar cost of the Parry)',30,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f4dcf15d-1ae2-416b-98b8-a11bd9684eb6','Mai','Taunt','','5PPPKKK','unique',430,121,213,-234,NULL,800,'','','Back Taunt is 430F start-up that spawns 8-hit Super projectile hitboxes on both sides of Mai; Projectile hitbox low to the ground that hits for 800 damage total (1500 damage if doing the held version) but is also hugely punishable even on hit; Deals no chip damage',31,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cee107b0-8abf-452c-b9dc-fd792835da49','Mai','LP Kachousen','','236LP','special',16,NULL,32,-7,-1,500,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.04; The fan has its own hurtbox and can be swatted away by the opponent''s strike or projectiles (top half of its hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes); Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the hold version for details); Leg (3~48F) and arm (16~42F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',32,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('eb1d18fa-6fb2-4d42-90db-0b74ce59faa1','Mai','LP Kachousen (stock)','','236LP (stock)','special',16,NULL,29,-3,1,600,'H','su3','Enhanced: 1 extra hit, +100 damage (600 damage total) and cannot be swatted away by the opponents attacks (functions like a regular projectile); 2-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.04; Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the stock + hold version for details); Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Leg (3~45F) and arm (16~42F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Only cancelable into SA3 on the first hit',33,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5ba0c5cc-bcc6-4fd4-ab38-5799c90dd206','Mai','MP Kachousen','','236MP','special',14,NULL,34,-9,-3,500,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.05; The fan has its own hurtbox and can be swatted away by the opponent''s strike or projectiles (top half of its hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes); Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the hold version for details); Leg (3~48F) and arm (14~40F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',34,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('bda86b40-1a61-4cd0-954c-120fba8762ea','Mai','MP Kachousen (stock)','','236MP (stock)','special',14,NULL,31,-5,-1,600,'H','su3','Enhanced: 1 extra hit, +100 damage (600 damage total) and cannot be swatted away by the opponents attacks (functions like a regular projectile); 2-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.05; Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the stock + hold version for details); Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Leg (3~45F) and arm (14~40F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Only cancelable into SA3 on the first hit',35,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('4ba1bd33-5209-48c3-971a-36f0f9264286','Mai','HP Kachousen','','236HP','special',12,NULL,36,-11,-5,500,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.07; The fan has its own hurtbox and can be swatted away by the opponent''s strike or projectiles (top half of its hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes); Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the hold version for details); Leg (3~48F) and arm (12~38F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',36,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('23c40781-b041-40fe-8b45-5d21138cfe4b','Mai','HP Kachousen (stock)','','236HP (stock)','special',12,NULL,33,-7,-3,600,'H','su3','Enhanced: 1 extra hit, +100 damage (600 damage total) and cannot be swatted away by the opponents attacks (functions like a regular projectile); 2-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.07; Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw a larger and more powerful version (see the stock + hold version for details); Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Leg (3~45F) and arm (12~38F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Only cancelable into SA3 on the first hit',37,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c2f12b3e-b0dc-4831-9952-662d9ec214c6','Mai','Kachousen (hold)','','236P (hold)','special',32,NULL,30,-1,1,500,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; This fan cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like a normal projectile would); The fan bounces upwards before falling back down (Projectile hitbox) after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); Projectile Speed and how far up the fan bounces upon hit / block varies depending on button strength; LP (Classic) / L (Modern): 0.04 speed and low fan bounce; MP (Classic) / M (Modern): 0.05 speed and medium fan bounce; HP (Classic) / H (Modern): 0.07 speed and high fan bounce; LP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 1F on hit / 3F on block | vs Crouch: 7F on hit / 9F on block; MP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 18F on hit / 20F on block | vs Crouch: 24F on hit / 26F on block; HP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 30F on hit / 32F on block | vs Crouch: 36F on hit / 38F on block; The frame gaps in fan bounces are slightly smaller on taller characters (1F smaller vs DJ | 2F smaller vs Zangief, Marisa and JP, meaning that a fully held LP fan bounce combos naturally on hit against those 3 characters when they''re standing); Leg (3-62F), body (19-31F), and arm (32-48F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Frame advantage listed on hit / block refers to the initial hit before the bounce (the bouncing fan deals 30F hitstun / 26F blockstun by itself, granting Mai potentially huge frame advantage); Any follow-up attack that Mai does overwrites the hitstun / blockstun of the bouncing fan',38,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d9226e9b-3e2f-4a45-8222-122c2682f8c3','Mai','Kachousen (stock + hold)','','236P (stock + hold)','special',32,NULL,30,-1,1,800,'H','su3','Enhanced: 1 extra hit and +100 damage (600 damage) before the bounce; 2-hit projectile; This fan cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like a normal projectile would); Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to the first 2 hits before the bounce; The fan bounces upwards before falling back down (Projectile hitbox) after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); Projectile Speed and how far up the fan bounces upon hit / block varies depending on button strength; LP (Classic) / L (Modern): 0.04 speed and low fan bounce; MP (Classic) / M (Modern): 0.05 speed and medium fan bounce; HP (Classic) / H (Modern): 0.07 speed and high fan bounce; LP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 9F on hit / 11F on block | vs Crouch: 15F on hit / 17F on block; MP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 26F on hit / 28F on block | vs Crouch: 32F on hit / 34F on block; HP fan bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 38F on hit / 40F on block | vs Crouch: 44F on hit / 46F on block; The frame gaps in fan bounces are slightly smaller on taller characters (1F smaller vs DJ | 2F smaller vs Zangief, Marisa and JP); Leg (32-62F) and arm (32-48F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; The bouncing fan does not trigger proximity guard (opponent can walk back during it) and counts as an air attack (anti-air invulnerable moves can pass through it)',39,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5fc9a60a-cba7-41ce-b31a-728bbf658aea','Mai','OD Kachousen','','236PP','special',12,NULL,30,-3,3,500,'H','su2, su3','1-hit OD projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.05; This fan cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like a normal OD projectile would); Bounces upwards before falling back down after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); Bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 15F on hit / 21F on block | vs Crouch: 21F on hit / 27F on block; The frame gaps in fan bounces are slightly smaller on taller characters (1F smaller vs DJ | 2F smaller vs Zangief, Marisa and JP); Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw extra fans (see the hold version and subsequent follow-up move for details); Leg hurtbox (12-37F) and upper body (15-27F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Only the initial hit is cancelable into SA2/SA3; The bouncing fan does not trigger proximity guard (opponent can walk back during it) and counts as an air attack (anti-air invulnerable moves can pass through it)',40,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5381d710-cc6f-47a9-a547-381b06513104','Mai','OD Kachousen (stock)','','236PP (stock)','special',12,NULL,30,1,3,800,'H','su2, su3','Enhanced: 1 extra hit, +100 damage (600 damage) before the bounce, and grants +1 frame advantage on block (regular OD version is -3 on block); 2-hit OD projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.05; This fan cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like a normal OD projectile would); Bounces upwards before falling back down after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); Bounce gaps on hit / block vs Standing: 23F on hit / 25F on block | vs Crouch: 29F on hit / 31F on block; The frame gaps in fan bounces are slightly smaller on taller characters (1F smaller vs DJ | 2F smaller vs Zangief, Marisa and JP); Holding the button for 19 frames lets Mai throw extra fans (see the stock + hold version and subsequent follow-up Midare Kachousen (stock) move for details)); Leg hurtbox (12-37F) and upper body (15-27F) hurtbox extensions are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Only the initial hit is cancelable into SA2/SA3; The bouncing fan does not trigger proximity guard (opponent can walk back during it) and counts as an air attack (anti-air invulnerable moves can pass through it)',41,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1acc1258-a7d7-42be-9cfc-ee85d5ab7958','Mai','OD Kachousen (hold)','','236PP (hold)','special',28,NULL,10,12,14,600,'H','su2, su3','Two separate 1-hit OD projectiles; Projectile Speed: 0.05; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; These fans cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like normal OD projectiles would); Can be followed-up with an extension (f+P) where Mai throws another two fans for no extra cost of resources (see the follow-up Midare Kachousen move for details); Arm/head hurtbox extensions on frames 28-58 are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state (but does not increase the current juggle state); Only the first hit is cancelable into SA2/SA3',42,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7030b3a5-6eb7-4009-9e9f-d34c5998e8d7','Mai','OD Kachousen (stock + hold)','','236PP (stock + hold)','special',28,NULL,10,46,45,700,'H','su2, su3','Enhanced: Both fans bounce upwards after connecting on hit / block and they all naturally combo for +100 extra damage (700 damage total); Two separate 1-hit OD projectiles; Projectile Speed: 0.05; These fans cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like normal OD projectiles would); Can be followed-up with an extension (f+P) where Mai throws another two fans for no extra cost of resources (see the follow-up Midare Kachousen move for details); Bounces upwards before falling back down after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (naturally combos and are all a true blockstring); Frame advantage varies depending on if the opponent is Standing / Crouching - vs Standing: +45 on hit / +46 on block | vs Crouching: +52 on hit / +53 on block; The frame advantage is slightly less on taller characters (DJ, JP, Marisa, Zangief); Arm/head hurtbox extensions on frames 28-58 are projectile invincible; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state (but does not increase the current juggle state); Only the first hit is cancelable into SA2/SA3; The bouncing fans do not trigger proximity guard (opponent can walk back during it) and counts as an air attack (anti-air invulnerable moves can pass through them)',43,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ddfd8ff1-efcf-44f8-9073-a92d8f19259f','Mai','Midare Kachousen','','236PP (hold) > 6P','special',28,NULL,24,0,NULL,1200,'H','','Two separate 1-hit OD projectiles (Four separate OD projectiles in total if you factor in the prior OD Kachousen); Projectile Speed: 0.072; These fans cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like normal OD projectiles would); Bounces upwards before falling back down after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); There are brief gaps on block before the follow-up fans connect (close range only), as well as before both the bouncing fans connect (the window of these gaps varies greatly depending on if the opponent is standing / crouching, as well as being few frames smaller for taller characters like DJ, JP, Marisa, Zangief); Arm/head hurtbox extensions on frames 28-79 are projectile invincible; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',44,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5e2839fe-1385-4765-b567-8df6b9aee9a8','Mai','Midare Kachousen (stock)','','236PP (stock + hold) > 6P','special',28,NULL,24,33,NULL,1400,'H','','Enhanced: Deals +200 extra damage on a regular hit (1400 damage total) with both the initial OD fans as well as the follow-up fans all bounce, resulting in 8 projectiles total (4 hitting directly, and 4 bouncing) which gives Mai huge frame advantage on block; Two separate 1-hit OD projectiles (Four separate OD projectiles in total if you factor in the prior OD Kachousen); Projectile Speed: 0.072; These fans cannot be swatted away by the opponent (behaves like normal OD projectiles would); Bounces upwards before falling back down after connecting with the opponent on hit or block (this gives Mai time to get in some follow-up hits or pressure); The frame advantage on block as well as the bouncing gap on block is far lower on taller characters (DJ, JP, Marisa, Zangief); Bounce gap on block for the final fan vs normal size characters Standing / Crouching: 9F vs Standing / 7F vs Crouching; Bounce gap on block for the final fan vs taller characters Standing / Crouching: 26F vs Standing / 7F vs Crouching; Frame advantage on block vs normal size characters Standing / Crouching: +33 on block vs Standing / +40 on block vs Crouching; Frame advantage on block vs taller characters Standing / Crouching: +15 on block vs Standing / +39 on block vs Crouching; Arm/head hurtbox extensions on frames 28-79 are projectile invincible; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',45,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e15070f3-d181-4865-9e1b-6b347c5591e4','Mai','LK Hishou Ryuuenjin','','623LK','special',5,5,15,-29,NULL,900,'H','','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-14; Airborne on frames 7-37 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Mai); Puts opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; 400 less damage (500 total) if only second hit connects on later active frames; Second hit whiffs on most crouch block (except tall bodies like Zangief, Marisa, JP, and DJ) resulting in slightly worse frame advantage (-32) and bit less chip and drive gauge damage',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('585b423d-73d3-4e12-a809-6d20147549da','Mai','LK Hishou Ryuuenjin (stock)','','623LK (stock)','special',5,5,15,-29,NULL,1000,'H','','Enhanced: 1 extra hit and 100 extra damage (1000 damage total) as well as slightly higher KDA (KD +31 instead of +29); Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-14; Airborne on frames 7-37 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Mai); Puts opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Less damage on later active frames (can whiff the first 1 or 2 hits); Last hit whiffs on most crouch block (except tall bodies like Zangief, Marisa, JP, and DJ) resulting in slightly worse frame advantage (-32) and bit less chip and drive gauge damage',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
