('78cb6cf1-a473-402d-bf0a-1e38e85cdc8d','Sagat','Stand MP','','5MP','normal',6,4,15,2,6,600,'H','','Sagat''s core combo / frametrap tool; High pushback on block (outside of throw range unless used from Drive Rush)',2,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('12f69eee-dec9-4918-a1c0-b59ef3bc6975','Sagat','Stand HP','','5HP','normal',15,4,22,-5,0,800,'H','tc','Huge range combo / poke tool with a hit-confirmable (19F hit confirm) Target Combo follow-up for a knockdown (results in +42 KD safe jumps in some combo routings); +3F extra recovery frames (25F) on whiff only; Extends a wide arm hurtbox on the first 10 recovery frames making it easily whiff punishable; Sagat stand HP privilege',3,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3b9adc17-5f89-4f83-9357-29052a493bdc','Sagat','Stand LK','','5LK','normal',7,2,15,-4,-1,400,'H','sp, su','Very far range for a stand LK (further range than his crouch MP) although slower than most light normals; +2F extra recovery frames (17F) on whiff only; Amazing whiff punish tool that combos into HP Tiger Uppercut at nearly any range on Punish Counter; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',4,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e3a358af-d2c3-4741-ad8d-5c65e01196a1','Sagat','Stand MK','','5MK','normal',11,4,19,-3,3,700,'H','tc','Very good poke button with a Target Combo follow-up for a knockdown; Slightly less range on crouching opponents (the tip of Sagat''s toe hitbox whiffs on crouch size hurtboxes); Extends a wide leg hurtbox on the first 10 recovery frames making it more easily whiff punishable',5,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('79862b06-5e86-4c70-a25b-410af2d6f7dc','Sagat','Stand HK','','5HK','normal',10,2,21,-5,1,600,'H','sp, su','Upper body / Kicking leg is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 9-15; Combo / Anti-air tool; Can''t hit cross-up (behind Sagat); Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Fully cancelable on both hits; Second hit does the full 900 damage by itself if the first hit whiffs (also applies to Drive damage and meter gain properties); Second hit whiffs on crouching opponents (resulting in -7 on block instead of -5); First hit forces stand (so the second hit can land); First hit deals extra hitstun over the second hit and thus has more combo potential when canceled (HK Tiger Nexus); First hit puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state (free juggle state if it initiates a juggle state); Second hit only has juggle potential when the first hit also connects; +4F extra recovery frames (25F) on whiff only (when both hits whiff); Extends a wide leg hurtbox on the first 11 recovery frames making it more easily whiff punishable; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',6,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('46188f0a-9120-4ffb-8a3e-9525aa9245b0','Sagat','Crouch LP','','2LP','normal',4,2,10,-1,5,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Great range for a 4F start-up jab; Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-5 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',7,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('12c0cc46-64c8-4333-8c7a-a2556181343d','Sagat','Crouch MP','','2MP','normal',7,3,16,-1,4,600,'H','sp, su, tc','Great combo / poke / buffer / pressure tool; Has two different Target Combo follow-ups for combo conversions (doesn''t combo into the HP follow-up without a Punish Counter or Drive Rush); +1F extra recovery frames (17F) on whiff or block; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-9 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air) and Projectile invincible on frames 1-14 (frames 15-26 can be hit by Sagat''s MP/HP Tiger Shot); Hitbox has significantly more range on active frames 2-3',8,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b6006c8f-1ab9-43ee-b6d7-29186849a5bf','Sagat','Crouch HP','','2HP','normal',11,4,21,-5,1,800,'H','sp, su','Great range combo / poke tool that''s fully cancelable and hit confirmable (18F hit confirm window); Hitbox has significantly more range on active frames 3-4; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-14 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air) and Projectile invincible on frames 1-19 (frames 20-35 can be hit by Sagat''s MP/HP Tiger Shot); CVS Crouch Fierce except now it''s fully cancelable (SF6 baby; Drive Rush brrrr)',9,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
