('e036e2e1-cce2-44c0-83aa-c9acf94d0122','Sagat','HP High Tiger Shot','','236HP','special',12,NULL,30,-1,-1,700,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.14; A very fast speed high traveling Fireball that whiffs on crouching opponents (although crouching moves that extend their hurtboxes upwards can still be hit); Can still hit a crouching opponent if used as a meaty on their first wake-up frame (opponent can still avoid and counter this by waking up with a crouching move); Has better frame advantage and faster start-up and recovery than the LP version (Low Tiger Shot); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; No hurtbox extension at all Sagat''s arms on frames 12-13 when initially throwing the fireball, and then slight projectile invincible hurtbox extension on his hand on frames 14-28; Minor hurtbox extension on the front leg on frames 14-42 (rest of the duration)',37,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('22c368cc-7d50-42b2-8bb8-0f18d774eff1','Sagat','OD High Tiger Shot','','236MPHP','special',21,NULL,27,6,NULL,1000,'H','su2, su3','3-hit OD projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.19; A super fast speed OD projectile that has good frame advantage on hit / block, and will beat most other OD projectiles due to having 3 hits; Very slow start-up for an OD projectile, but has a lot of strengths to make up for that fact; Puts opponents into a limited juggle state (can juggle into another OD High Tiger Shot, or Level 1 Super from anywhere on the screen); No hurtbox extension at all Sagat''s arms on frames 21-24 when initially throwing the fireball, and then slight projectile invincible hurtbox extension on his hand on frames 25-41; Minor hurtbox extension on the front leg on frames 25-48 (rest of the duration); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo, and counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into; The 20% starter scaling does not apply if the 3rd hit begins the combo (like clashing with a 2-hit OD fireball or breaking Drive Impact armor)',38,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1d8510cd-5b68-4d94-89cc-86b62fa55fdd','Sagat','LP Tiger Uppercut','','623LP','special',5,10,35,-37,NULL,1100,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-14; Airborne on frames 9-49 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Sagat); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 300 less damage (800) on later active frames 4-10; Cancelable into Level 3 Super on active frames 1-2 only; Incurs 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',39,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f04aaf41-46e2-466a-bf29-a055b4edbd46','Sagat','MP Tiger Uppercut','','623MP','special',10,10,40,-45,NULL,1400,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-13; Airborne on frames 14-59 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Sagat); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 600 less damage (800) on later active frames 4-10; Cancelable into Level 3 Super on active frames 1-2 only; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',40,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a3be30e1-8708-4c78-ab82-c5dd9a68b5f7','Sagat','HP Tiger Uppercut','','623HP','special',18,10,40,-45,NULL,1600,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-21; Airborne on frames 22-67 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Sagat); Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 600 less damage (1000) on later active frames 3-10; Cancelable into Level 3 Super on active frames 1-2 only; Can be held to gain increased damage and properties (see hold version); Incurs 10% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',41,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('9637c873-562d-4b24-9e98-83ede4b0be78','Sagat','HP Tiger Uppercut (hold)','','623HP (hold)','special',35,10,40,-45,NULL,1800,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-9 while holding HP and then again on frames 1-11 after releasing HP (if HP is not released early, the air invincibility frames are: 1-9 and 28-38); Airborne on frames 39-84 or frames 12-57 if HP is released early (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Sagat); HP has to be held for at least 24 frames in order to do the fully held version; Releasing HP early results in a normal HP DP with 8F start-up; Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Does not transition into the Wall Splat version if hitting on later active frames 3-10, resulting in 1100 less damage (1700); Cancelable into Level 3 Super on active frames 1-2 only; Wall Splat is a fixed +23 HKD and creates spacing for Sagat to start zoning again',42,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('be041245-a9a3-4889-aea1-c6c8cbcac850','Sagat','OD Tiger Uppercut','','623PP','special',8,2,38,-43,NULL,1600,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-12; Airborne on frames 12-57 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Sagat); Deals less damage on later active frames (first hit does the biggest chunk of damage); Slower start-up than the other shoto OD DPs, making Sagat unable to punish some moves like Ken''s Jinrai Kicks',43,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('518a2792-557c-4583-bed6-a5719e33fb9b','Sagat','LK Tiger Knee Crush','','236LK','special',14,11,3,-8,NULL,800,'H','','Airborne on frames 13-27; Lower body projectile invincibility on frames 13-26 (can leap over projectiles); No hurtbox on front leg just before Sagat leaps forward (frames 10-12) which helps to avoid low pokes; Range: 1.54~2.41; Improved oki and frame advantage on (up to +2 on block) when spaced out or hitting on later active frames; Whiffs on crouching opponents on active frames 2-10 making this very easy to space for +2 on block against crouch blocking opponents; Suffers 3F extra recovery frames (21F total) against armored attacks (weaker against things like Drive Impact); Can be used to hop over and switch sides with a knocked down opponent in some situations; Puts opponent into a limited juggle state; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',44,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('cb9ce895-8cfd-4468-b491-689d02f8778b','Sagat','MK Tiger Knee Crush','','236MK','special',18,11,3,-7,NULL,1000,'H','','Airborne on frames 16-31; Lower body projectile invincibility on frames 18-30 (can leap over projectiles); No hurtbox on front leg just before Sagat leaps forward (frames 14-15) which helps to avoid low pokes; Range: 1.67~2.97; Improved oki and frame advantage on (up to +3 on block) when spaced out or hitting on later active frames; Whiffs on crouching opponents on active frames 2-9 making this very easy to space for +2 on block against crouch blocking opponents; Suffers 3F extra recovery frames (21F total) against armored attacks (weaker against things like Drive Impact); Can be used to hop over and switch sides with a knocked down opponent in some situations; Puts opponent into a limited juggle state; Sets up a KD +42 safe jump anywhere on the screen when juggled at a specific height (like after d+MP > HP OTG bounce); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',45,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a85966ac-d1a7-48a8-bc5a-f613230babbb','Sagat','HK Tiger Knee Crush','','236HK','special',22,4,3,-5,NULL,1400,'H','su3','Airborne on frames 24-43; Lower body projectile invincibility on frames 27-41 (can leap over projectiles); Range: 1.74~3.90; Improved oki and frame advantage on (up to +5 on block) when spaced out or hitting on later active frames; Deals 500 less damage (900) when spaced out so the first knee hit doesn''t connect; Knockdown advantage is different and more variable when spaced out and connecting with just the second hit (very relevant in certain combo / juggle routes); Second hit whiffs on crouching opponents on active frames 1-9 making this very easy to space for +4 on block against crouch blocking opponents; Puts opponent into a limited juggle state; Sets up a KD +42 safe jump near the corner when juggled at a specific height (like after d+MP > HP OTG bounce)',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a6303692-abe8-4c57-9b77-32d75888a66a','Sagat','OD Tiger Knee Crush','','236KK','special',19,3,2,-2,NULL,1600,'H','su2, su3','Airborne on frames 21-38; Lower body projectile invincibility on frames 22-37 (can leap over projectiles); Range: 1.62~3.87; Improved frame advantage on block (up to +2) when spaced out or hitting on later active frames; Transitions into a follow-up attack if the first hit connects on hit that results in +66 KD Tumble (can OTG juggle with LP DP afterwards); Worse oki and damage when spaced out so the initial knee strike doesn''t reach; Full damage if the first knee strike lands is 1600, but the second half only deals 500 (1 hit) or 1000 (2 hits) damage depending on spacing; Second hit whiffs on crouching opponents on active frames 2-10 making this effectively +1 on block against crouching opponents (even when used from up close); Puts opponent into a limited juggle state; Incurs 30% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo, and counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ffd33a49-741a-453f-8f57-94d59387c43f','Sagat','LK Tiger Nexus','','214LK','special',17,3,23,-5,2,500,'H','su3','Doesn''t combo naturally into the Nova Tiger (f+HK) follow-up (leaves an interruptible gap on block even in Burnout); Only version comboable into from stand LP (whiffs after 3 chained lights); Follow-ups cannot be performed on whiff (unlike Ken''s Jinrai); Counter-hit and Punish Counter put the opponent into a limited juggle state (this allows Nova Tiger (f+HK) to combo); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',48,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8fab74cb-57db-42bb-a195-3b5d6bf6e17d','Sagat','MK Tiger Nexus','','214MK','special',20,3,23,-5,2,500,'H','su3','Doesn''t combo naturally into the Nova Tiger (f+HK) follow-up (leaves an interruptible gap on block even in Burnout); Follow-ups cannot be performed on whiff (unlike Ken''s Jinrai); Counter-hit and Punish Counter put the opponent into a limited juggle state (this allows Nova Tiger (f+HK) to combo); Combos from canceled stand HK / crouch MP / crouch HP (also a DI-safe frametrap on block from stand HK / crouch HP); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',49,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('df48327a-3fda-4a5b-a684-989ceb24f275','Sagat','HK Tiger Nexus','','214HK','special',28,3,20,-3,4,500,'H','su3','Combos naturally into the Nova Tiger (f+HK) follow-up; Very slow start-up makes this only naturally comboable from the first hit of Stand HK, or other Punish / Drive Rush related cancels; Blocked cancels into this move are always interruptible (except for Drive Rush stand HK / crouch MP / crouch HP against a burned out opponent); Follow-ups cannot be performed on whiff (unlike Ken''s Jinrai); +2F extra recovery frames (22F) when Perfect Parried; If the first hit is Perfect Parried, the second hit will interrupt any attack slower than 5F startup',50,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('944f9214-d610-4f9f-85c5-9a26c65d8dd7','Sagat','Mighty Tiger','','214K > 6LK','special',15,3,22,-5,3,800,'M','su3','Overhead; Frametraps the opponent trying to interrupt the other two follow-ups on block (2F gap, 3F trades from LK/MK Nexus and 0F gap, 1F trades from HK Nexus); Puts airborne opponents into an OTG limited juggle state; Safe on block if the opponent is in Burnout (can only frametrap by delaying the f+LK input after LK/MK Nexus); Drive Impact punishes the overhead after LK/MK Nexus on block (safe after HK Nexus unless the f+LK input is delayed); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',51,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e43e545c-ec8c-48d9-8076-bf368fbb8c03','Sagat','Greedy Tiger','','214K > 6MK','special',17,3,17,4,NULL,1000,'H','su3','Plus on block follow-up that whiffs on crouching opponents (resulting in -19 on hit / -26 on block from LK/MK version and -17 on hit / -24 on block from HK version); +2F extra recovery frames (19F) on whiff only; 4F gap on block (5F trades) after LK/MK Tiger Nexus, so can be interrupted by standing/crouching 4F jabs; 2F gap on block (3F trades) after HK Tiger Nexus for a frametrap against standing 4F lights (but still loses to crouching attacks); Counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state (can follow up with LP/OD Tiger Uppercut in the corner); Safe to reversal Drive Impact after Tiger Nexus on block',52,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d9db069a-01c0-4598-9860-f04cabe27dba','Sagat','Nova Tiger','','214K > 6HK','special',21,3,19,2,NULL,800,'H','su3','Launcher that''s advantageous on block and hits both Standing and Crouching; Despite its obvious strengths, this move has gaps on block and is unsafe to things like Drive Impact / Perfect Parry / invincible reversals; Only combos naturally from HK Tiger Nexus (requires juggle state from LK / MK versions); Frametraps when used from HK Tiger Nexus against a burned out opponent; Counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state',53,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a9f2661b-8afc-4468-841c-369c3b7a56fd','Sagat','OD Tiger Nexus','','214KK','special',23,3,20,-3,4,500,'H','su2, su3','Basically just a faster start-up of the HK version, allowing this to be combo''d into from more options like stand HK / crouch HP; Combos naturally into all the follow-ups; Blocked cancels into this move cannot frametrap 4F attacks without Drive Rush or Burnout; +2F extra recovery frames (22F) when Perfect Parried; If the first hit is Perfect Parried, the second hit will interrupt any attack slower than 5F startup',54,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f39828e2-c4f7-4be9-b6e9-6c131a53811c','Sagat','OD Mighty Tiger','','214KK > 6LK','special',15,3,22,-5,3,1300,'M','su2, su3','Overhead; Frametraps the opponent trying to interrupt the other two follow-ups on block (0F gap, 1F trades); Puts airborne opponents into an OTG limited juggle state; Safe on block if the opponent is in Burnout (but can no longer frametrap); Safe against reversal Drive Impact unless the f+LK input is delayed; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',55,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('de82987b-ecac-49eb-a986-e4664bfcdb15','Sagat','OD Greedy Tiger','','214KK > 6MK','special',17,3,17,4,NULL,1500,'H','su2, su3','Plus on block follow-up that whiffs on crouching opponents (resulting in -17 on hit / -24 on block); +2F extra recovery frames (19F) on whiff only; 2F gap on block (3F trades) for a frametrap against standing 4F lights (but still loses to crouching attacks); Counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state (can follow up with LP/OD Tiger Uppercut in the corner); Safe to reversal Drive Impact after OD Tiger Nexus on block',56,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('84a386ea-763c-4822-a2c2-b50a95fa2065','Sagat','OD Nova Tiger','','214KK > 6HK','special',21,3,19,2,NULL,1300,'H','su2, su3','Launcher that''s advantageous on block and hits both Standing and Crouching; Despite its obvious strengths, this move has gaps on block and is unsafe to things like Drive Impact / Perfect Parry / invincible reversals; Combos naturally from OD Tiger Nexus; Frametraps when used against a burned out opponent; Counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into; Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state',57,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7a7c3cc7-bd0a-4dcb-ba83-e2c75f93ebba','Sagat','Tiger Cannon','','236236P','super',13,NULL,96,-31,NULL,2200,'H','','Strike and Throw invincible on frames 1-13; 8-hit Super projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.23; Projectile speed is not affected by button strength; Armor Break; Depletes 0.5 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; Can be used while OD High/Low Tiger Shot is on the screen (but not meterless Tiger Shot)',58,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ea12fa5c-5e58-4949-be9f-463c79dd4ddd','Sagat','Savage Tiger','','214214K','super',10,5,73,-58,NULL,3000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-14; Armor Break; A multi-purpose Super with 4 different variations to choose from depending on which direction is held during the animation where Sagat clutches the opponent''s head; Neutral input: Savage Tiger Raid (Damage / Combo ender); Forward input: Savage Tiger Zenith (Launcher / Combo extension); Back input: Savage Tiger Pendulum (Side-switch); Down input: Savage Tiger Stomp (Better oki); See the four respective follow-ups to this Super for more details on each version; Sagat''s most consistent reversal Super at 10F startup; Can be used from about half screen to counter projectiles; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent on all versions',59,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b8adf2c8-ab95-43e2-a37b-f29af7fd5e82','Sagat','Savage Tiger Raid','','214214K > 5','super',10,5,73,-58,NULL,3000,'H','','This follow-up is used for just straight up damage or as a combo ender; Good corner carry (over half screen) but no oki afterward; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent',60,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('be248792-d237-4131-8c49-7ecb43a544d7','Sagat','Savage Tiger Zenith','','214214K > 6','super',10,5,73,-58,NULL,1700,'H','','This follow-up launches them into a juggle scenario with follow-up combos / corner carry; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; Follow-up juggle routes generally deal a bit less damage than Tiger Raid in exchange for oki, corner carry, and rebuilding some Super meter; Most flexible option in terms of options possible afterwards?; Incurs 50% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo and counts as 4 hits of damage scaling when combo''d into',61,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('158e07cd-de30-445c-9978-b1d10e3a3be7','Sagat','Savage Tiger Pendulum','','214214K > 4','super',10,5,73,-58,NULL,2700,'H','','This follow-up is used to swap sides with the opponent at the cost of oki and 300 damage; Useful when cornered and low on resources (Burnout); Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent',62,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a3492321-8136-4ac8-ace9-8f748d85e8b2','Sagat','Savage Tiger Stomp','','214214K > 2','super',10,5,73,-58,NULL,2700,'H','','This follow-up gives a Hard Knockdown (HKD; opponent can''t back-roll) and leaves Sagat right next to the opponent for some pressure at the cost of 300 damage; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent',63,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2a272f96-fec7-4e40-ae55-f889ed677ba2','Sagat','Tiger Vanquisher','','236236K','super',12,4,67,-51,NULL,4000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-15; Armor Break; Depletes 1.5 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~1.9 Drive Bars for Sagat; Can be used from about half screen to counter projectiles; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials (20%~40% scaling when canceled into from a DP combo starter); Only 2F start-up when canceled into from Tiger Uppercut',64,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('78f47e65-c356-4d1b-8d69-dbab29abec4b','Sagat','Tiger Vanquisher (Critical Art)','','236236K (CA)','super',12,4,67,-51,NULL,4500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-15; Critical Art does +500 extra damage over regular version; Armor Break; Depletes 2 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates ~1.9 Drive Bars for Sagat; Can be used from about half screen to counter projectiles; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials (20%~40% scaling when canceled into from a DP combo starter); Only 2F start-up when canceled into from Tiger Uppercut',65,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('a441ebbf-b183-4a28-a119-e44b0eb0864d','Terry','Stand LP','','5LP','normal',4,3,7,-1,4,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Further range than 2LP makes this relevant in some combo / blockstring routes',1,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8cb441fd-7ac5-4138-bc25-a19be201d9c3','Terry','Stand MP','','5MP','normal',7,3,16,-3,2,700,'H','sp, su, tc','Core combo / buffer tool that leads into various Target Combos; Can be a good poke / bully tool in close range, especially in Burnout due to its small pushback on block',2,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e3fae29d-b964-4425-adb8-f93c9ee153bc','Terry','Stand HP','','5HP','normal',9,1,18,1,2,800,'H','sp, su','2-hit combo / buffer / pressure tool that''s very easily hit confirmed if both hits connect; Cancelable on both hits; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; First hit has increased hitstun for combo potential (second hit won''t combo naturally into things like HK Power Charge); Solid hitbox priority can make this a good counter-poke tool in neutral; First hit has less range than the second (only the second hit will connect outside of close range); Hitstop for the second hit is +3 extra (13F) if the first hit whiffs; Leaves Terry slightly outside throw range when blocked out of Drive Rush (but he can microwalk to throw while beating 4F normals)',3,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('997458ac-1a7f-4c94-a419-d63a1709c955','Terry','Stand LK','','5LK','normal',5,2,12,-2,2,300,'H','sp, su','Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Terry''s main way of comboing into the spaced out LK Power Charge for combo extensions',4,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7d9191aa-d030-41d3-842d-bbbd0b32d8d4','Terry','Stand MK','','5MK','normal',9,3,18,-2,5,700,'H','','Core combo and poke tool; Terry lifts up his front leg hurtbox on frames 3-20 making this a good tool against low attacks; Can easily hit confirm this on Counter-Hit into SA1 (Buster Wolf) or on Punish Counter into Fire Kick (2MK > 2HK) if in range of 2MK',5,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f9199346-9d74-4305-9b19-cf9018d90315','Terry','Stand HK','','5HK','normal',12,4,21,-4,1,900,'H','','Solid bully tool with decent range and hitbox priority as well as doing good Drive Gauge chip on block; Decent anti-air on frames 14-15 (think Chun-Li stand HK but worse); Causes a crumple-like free juggle state on a grounded Punish Counter (+18 frames to connect a follow-up combo before the opponent is knocked down); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on Punish Counter; The brief extended leg hurtbox on frame 11 of start-up (1F before active) is strike invincible (cannot counter-poke projectiles)',6,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('163ad881-e695-4c90-852a-5b6e878d31e8','Terry','Crouch LP','','2LP','normal',4,3,8,-1,4,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Terry''s only way to naturally combo into MP Burn Knuckle from LP/2LK starters; Shortest range of Terry''s light attacks; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-6 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',7,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2da4bffa-ed0a-4a8e-809c-09a82dc7b2cb','Terry','Crouch MP','','2MP','normal',6,4,13,-1,5,600,'H','sp, su','Fantastic combo / poke / buffer / oki tool; +1 extra recovery frames (14F) on whiff or block; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-9 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',8,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e2280a52-ec36-4916-9fa1-f9467a561a1d','Terry','Crouch HP','','2HP','normal',8,4,20,-4,1,800,'H','sp, su','Forces stand on hit; Solid anti-air on frames 10-13 (but has no air invincibility frames); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Terry); Only cancelable on the first two active frames; Cancel window can be delayed manually when canceling into OD Power Wave to adjust positioning during combos and create more combo routes; Short horizontal range (can only be combo''d into from up close); Framedata listed in parentheses refers to the version that plays out on whiff or on active frames 3-6 (shorter duration overall if active frames 1-2 connect on hit or block)',9,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e1daa5c8-123d-4151-a810-e6956187c0de','Terry','Crouch LK','','2LK','normal',5,2,11,-2,3,200,'L','ch','Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Very small pushback, strong hitbox priority, good range, and a +3 on hit low attack, makes this Terry''s ideal light combo / blockstring starter',10,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8bd47bfa-f7e5-4aec-820c-7b4a67ae3ba8','Terry','Crouch MK','','2MK','normal',8,3,19,-6,-2,500,'L','sp, su, tc','Fantastic range for a crouch MK; Cancelable into a HK Target Combo that launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Incurs a 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',11,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('8c1acae3-e801-44d4-8755-b39e95388228','Terry','Crouch HK','','2HK','normal',10,3,24,-11,NULL,900,'L','','Has strong hitbox priority for counter-poking purposes; Situational anti-air from further away jumps; Has some Juggle potential naturally without Drive Rush',12,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e2185c9e-1528-46c2-a065-e88b99375c3c','Terry','Jump LP','','8LP','normal',4,7,NULL,2,6,300,'M','','Fast air-to-air option',13,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('be1c13fd-e5b3-4d94-89d6-a4709c6ca105','Terry','Jump MP','','8MP','normal',7,4,NULL,7,11,700,'M','','Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Big air-to-air hitboxes; Can only just barely connect on standing grounded opponents on the last active frame',14,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f9970734-d255-46b5-bcd8-d7c22aa4b549','Terry','Jump HP','','8HP','normal',9,6,NULL,5,9,800,'M','','Spikes down airborne opponents on Counter-Hit or Punish Counter; Strong hitbox priority for vertical approaches',15,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('870ec287-ff5e-4043-9768-253f9903754b','Terry','Jump LK','','8LK','normal',5,7,NULL,3,7,300,'M','','Another quick air-to-air option',16,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7d9f13e9-7711-4d5e-95d1-d45f0f59bbe9','Terry','Jump MK','','8MK','normal',7,6,NULL,4,8,500,'M','','Cross-up that also has great hitbox priority on the front',17,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('efb15ae7-ac39-440c-a66f-ec1f63209b13','Terry','Jump HK','','8HK','normal',10,7,NULL,5,9,800,'M','','Terry''s strongest jump-in; Furthest horizontal reach and also has fantastic hitbox priority for both horizontal and vertical approaches',18,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c00780ef-3dfd-4758-8cd6-f00c564bdc0d','Terry','Hammer Punch','','6HP','normal',22,3,19,-2,2,800,'M','','Just a pretty standard Overhead (can meaty last active frame to do jab combo follow-ups); BUG: Drive gauge / Super meter values are all out of wack on this move (this was likely scripted as a Medium command normal at some point and Capcom forgot to adjust all its values properly)',19,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('bc004b63-1e92-48dd-a5c2-0af2d5ab2d0e','Terry','Power Drive','','5MP > 5HP','normal',15,3,22,-5,NULL,1100,'H','','Knocks down opponent on hit; 2F gap on block (frametrap); Relatively safe on block if spaced out (many stand LK can punish if not spaced out properly); Can be hit confirmed (but this is very hard at 16F hit confirm window); Second hit incurs 30% immediate damage scaling when combo''d into from stand MP',20,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d28ea947-75f1-4a10-872a-ff7345a1bb71','Terry','Power Shoot','','5MP > 5HK','normal',18,3,31,-14,NULL,600,'H','tc','Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Counts as 2 hits of damage scaling when both hits land; Not a natural combo (requires at least Drive Rush / Counter-Hit / hitting meaty on 2nd active frame of stand MP); Terry can do certain combo routes to setup the spacing required to hit MP on the second active frame for the whole Power Dunk combo to work; 4F gap on block (5F attacks trade)',21,datetime('now'),datetime('now'));
INSERT INTO frame_data (id,character,move_name,move_name_jp,input,category,startup,active,recovery,on_block,on_hit,damage,guard,cancel_into,notes,sort_order,updated_at,created_at) VALUES
('06a14eee-a072-4417-b79f-7ba167659cb0','Terry','Power Dunk','','5MP > 5HK > 5HK','normal',18,3,33,NULL,NULL,2210,'H','','Only possible to perform on hit; Great combo extension tool that gives decent corner carry and oki; Last hit (Power Dunk!) can be manually delayed to hit a 2-frame Just Frame window to deal 140 extra damage (2350 total) and get increased drive / super gain (this Just Frame version is indicated by an increased screen shake and hitstop upon impact); Power Dunk follow-up is on a 6F cancel window and the Just Frame input is on frames 3-4 on that window, while frames 1-2 and 5-6 result in a regular Power Dunk; Try using visual queues to help with the Just Frame timing, for example pressing the button when Terry''s kicking leg touches the ground; KDA (Knockdown Advantage) varies depending on how delayed the Power Dunk is performed (less KDA the more it is delayed)',22,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b1edd654-96cc-4193-86cd-deb938b71dca','Terry','Fire Kick','','2MK > 2HK','normal',13,2,28,-16,NULL,500,'L*H','sp, su','Low target combo that''s fully cancelable and launches opponent into a limited juggle state on hit',23,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d3086002-70af-40c6-8497-308e65cb064f','Terry','Passing Sway','','5MP > 5MK','normal',13,2,27,-12,-3,400,'H','tc','Useful mixup / reset / sideswap tool; Terry steps into the background after second hit (MK) on HIT only on frames 20-40 (Terry is fully invincible and has no collision boxes during this period); 1F gap between hits on block (up to 2F if manually delayed); Cancelable into two different follow-ups (MP or MK) on HIT only; The cancel window for the follow-ups is on frames 30-36 (delaying the follow-ups can make the opponent''s invincible Reversals whiff entirely); While the follow-ups can be countered with a strike / air invincible Reversals and Perfect Parry, if Terry delays the follow-ups then on paper he can beat everything in the game except for Lily''s SA2 (the only way for the opponent to otherwise counter the delayed follow-ups is to also delay their own moves, and thus the mind games begin)',24,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('e07cd7ef-a8ec-44f2-b739-78505e5446d1','Terry','Passing Sway > Jumping Lariat','','5MP > 5MK > 5MP','normal',24,2,18,3,4,1000,'H','','Fully invincible and has no collision during entire start-up and active frames (this can be utilized to avoid every Reversal attempt in the game except for Lily''s SA2); Hold forward to increase the distance Terry moves forward before swinging (can hold forward to go behind the opponent and intentionally whiff the MP follow-up, resulting in -23~29 on whiff); Cannot hit cross-up (MK follow-up is designed for that); Doesn''t combo on hit from MP > MK; 3-9 frames gap on hit depending on how much the follow-up is delayed (although this gap is not that relevant since Terry is still fully invincible during it); A cornered opponent can hold forward to make this follow-up whiff no matter whether Terry holds forward or back (works mid-screen as well if Terry delays the Jumping Lariat follow-up)',25,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2ea7f390-2430-4f64-9e94-61baf1e8fb81','Terry','Passing Sway > Jumping Knee','','5MP > 5MK > 5MK','normal',24,2,20,-2,3,1000,'H','','Fully invincible and has no collision during entire start-up and active frames (this can be utilized to avoid every Reversal attempt in the game except for Lily''s SA2); Hold forward to increase the distance Terry moves forward before swinging (not holding forward makes Terry whiff the knee and stay in front of the opponent, resulting in -25~31 on whiff); Cannot hit in the front (can only hit cross-up behind the opponent); Doesn''t combo on hit from MP > MK; 3-9 frames gap on hit depending on how much the follow-up is delayed (although this gap is not that relevant since Terry is still fully invincible during it); An opponent with 0.043 forward walk speed or faster can hold forward to block this follow-up behind them even if Terry holds back during the Jumping Knee follow-up (all characters can do this if Terry delays the Jumping Knee follow-up)',26,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6c0e8f32-afab-4350-9a67-f93eb206ff55','Terry','Grasping Upper','','LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Throw loop (corner / quick rise only): Dash forward for +3 strike/throw mix or walk forward to manually time it; Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',27,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b8e465bb-29a8-4955-acc2-9eafcff83209','Terry','Buster Throw','','4LPLK','throw',5,3,23,NULL,NULL,1200,'T','','Throw oki (corner / quick rise only): Drive Rush strike / throw mix; Gets +70% damage increase (2040 damage), HKD (denies back-roll option on wake-up), and depletes 1 bar of Drive Gauge on a Punish Counter',28,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('76816ec9-0c7c-4871-8a3c-4fa89ad4b783','Terry','Drive Impact: Back Spin Kick','','HPHK','unique',26,2,35,-3,NULL,800,'H','','2 hits of armor on frames 1-27; Damages opponents Drive Gauge on Block (1/2 bar) | Hit (1 bar) | Counter-Hit (1.25 bar) | Punish Counter (1.5 bar); Knocks down on hit; Crumples on Punish Counter or after absorbing at least 1 attack during start-up (+21 frames before the crumple state goes airborne, followed by airborne state on frames 22-46 before they are grounded) which counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; If the armor absorbs an attack it slows the overall start-up by 1F (27F total instead of 26F); Pushes the opponent far back on hit or block and causes a wall splat if they hit the wall; Wall Splat on block adds 20% damage penalty on the next hit; Wall splats on hit or during Burnout counts as 2 hits of damage scaling; Wall Splat puts opponent into a special juggle state where the next move juggles them even if it doesn''t normally (similar juggle rules as from Drive Rush); Does not cause wall splat if combo''d into from other moves or unblockable setups (Lock); Puts airborne opponents into a long spinning free juggle state when hit as a Punish Counter; Regular KDA without a Wall Splat: +35 KD; Corner wall splat on HIT: +65 KD | Block: +72 HKD; KDA can vary greatly depending on how high the opponent wall splats (higher KDA the higher they wall splat); Can clash with other Drive Impacts if they collide on the same active frame (start at exactly the same time); Costs 1 bar of Drive Gauge; The scrub killer',29,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('088e3cba-59b2-47f9-b468-8c71ca0a16ad','Terry','Drive Reversal: Back Knuckle','','6HPHK','unique',20,3,26,-6,NULL,500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-22 (frames 1-20 when used on wake-up as a Reversal); Armor Break (blows through all armor like Drive Impact); Can be performed during blockstun or from a successful parry (trying to Drive Reversal after the blockstun is over will result in a Drive Impact); Can also be performed during wake-up as a Reversal, doing it this way speeds up the start-up frames by 2 frames (18F start-up instead of 20F); Drive Reversal immediately removes the current blockstun you''re in and starts the attack; Causes a 4F screen freeze that occurs after the 6th start-up frame, which can mess up the opponents input timing, or enable them to do a simple input OS to counter the Drive Reversal; Safe on block (-2) when used against an opponent currently in Burnout; Costs 2 bars of Drive Gauge',30,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('84ab6976-ac3f-497a-bf99-61d51c9a482d','Terry','Drive Parry','','MPMK','unique',1,12,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Parries all strikes and projectiles (high and low) from frame 1; 12F parry window (can hold the parry to extend the parry window); Perfect Parry occurs on the first 2 active frames (cannot achieve Perfect Parry if you buffer into parry by holding it during Reversal windows; Perfect Parries have to be timed properly); Can still hold charge directions during Parry; Can block during the recovery frames of a regular parry (can still get hit during the recovery frames if you don''t block correctly); Getting thrown or hit at any point during the recovery frames of a whiffed parry attempt results in a Punish Counter; Successfully parrying a move puts you into the same amount of blockstun as that move would regularly do on block (but a Perfect Parry has only 1F of recovery); Throw invincible during the recovery of a successful parry (just like during blockstun); Perfect Parrying a strike has only 1F of recovery and disables the opponent from canceling their attack (basically a guaranteed punish opportunity); After a successful Perfect Parry, you suffer a 50% penalty to your Damage, Drive Gauge Generation, and Drive Gauge Damage on any of your following attacks when punishing the opponent (in addition, both you and the opponent suffer a 20% penalty to their Super Meter gain during this period); Fully invincible for 6F after a successful Perfect Parry against a strike, during which period you can cancel into anything you want and it carries over the brief invincibility frames; Perfect Parrying projectiles puts you into fixed 10 frames of recovery and applies the same 50% scaling penalties (and 20% Super Meter penalty) on your following attacks when punishing the opponent; Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will result in a regular parry for the strike attack (effectively ignoring the projectile''s hitstop / blockstun); Perfect Parrying a Strike and Projectile on the same frame will give a screen freeze like you Perfect Parried a Strike, but still give you 10F recovery as if you had Perfect Parried a Projectile; Can cancel into Drive Rush during active frames 3 and onward (fastest Drive Rush method is to buffer a forward input before doing parry + forward again); Can cancel into Drive Reversal from a successful parry (just like you can normally during blockstun); Costs 1/2 bar Drive Gauge (continues to deplete Drive Gauge as you hold the Parry); You lose the parry if you go into Burnout from the Drive Gauge cost; Rewards 1 bar Drive Gauge (1/2 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a strike; Rewards 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge (0 bar total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successfully parrying a projectile; Rewards 2 bars of Drive Gauge (1.5 bars total after factoring in the initial parry cost) for successful parrying a Drive Impact; Successfully parrying a strike attack splits the regular block pushback between both players (while Perfect Parrying a strike removes all of its pushback); Successfully parrying a projectile or Drive Impact reduces the pushback of it by half (while Perfect Parrying a projectile or Drive Impact removes all of its pushback); Your hurtbox and throw box expand slightly towards the opponent for the entire duration of the Parry (Throw box extension starts instantly on frame 1, while the Hurtbox extension starts on frame 3, after the initial 2F Perfect Parry window); Parrying while crouching maintains a regular crouch hurtbox for the first 2 frames of the parry (during the initial Perfect Parry window)',31,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d6843342-748e-4464-9a52-4b436f8ea302','Terry','Drive Rush','','MPMK / 66 (cancel)','unique',9,45,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','Dashes forward and enhances the next normal used out of the Drive Rush with +4 extra hitstun / blockstun (some moves also get unique properties enhanced such as juggle state); The +4 bonus frame advantage gained from a Drive Rush enhanced move also stacks with any bonus frame advantage that move may have gained from Counter-Hit or Punish Counter; Cancelable into from special cancelable grounded normals; Drive Rush maintains buffers (freezes the buffer window) during it start-up and freeze frames - This allows players to do things normally not possible within the normal buffer windows, such as Drive Rushing into a charge special; The initial freeze frames that occur when a Drive Rush happens eats the opponents inputs; Framedata shown in parentheses refers to the Drive Rush version used from a Parry; Drive Rush recovery frames is only 24F total (23F if done from a Parry) - but the enhanced dash itself is 46F total (45F if done from Parry) and you can cancel it as early as frame 9 (frame 11 if done from a Parry); You stop building any form of Drive Gauge on your attacks after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (but you still continue to build drive gauge as normal if you did Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Applies extra damage scaling penalty after using a Drive Rush in the MIDDLE of a combo (no damage scaling if you use Drive Rush at the START of a combo); Costs 3 bars of Drive Gauge if canceled into from a move; Costs 1/2 bar of Drive Gauge if canceled into from Parry (for a total of 1 bar of Drive Gauge when you factor in the initial 1/2 bar cost of the Parry)',32,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f3434d10-2a35-40fd-a0e7-56f5c4a35fab','Terry','Taunt','','5PPPKKK','unique',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',33,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('f31e5c99-7bb1-41c0-8959-c38a6983445e','Terry','LP Power Wave','','236LP','special',14,NULL,35,-9,-3,600,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.06; Travels full-screen; Goes underneath most traditional fireballs (clashes with Juri''s Fireball); Extended arm hurtbox on frames 14-37 is Projectile invincible; No head hurtbox on frames 11-41 while Terry is leaning over; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',34,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('14cdea8f-3126-4bc1-8054-a03dc0f8ac50','Terry','MP Power Wave','','236MP','special',16,14,32,-6,0,700,'H','su3','1-hit projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.02~0.21 (starts slow and then speeds up a lot as it goes forward); Travels ~60% screen length very fast, but dissipates quickly; Does not go underneath fireballs (clashes with regular fireballs); Extended arm hurtbox on frames 21-39 is Projectile invincible; No head hurtbox on frames 11-41 while Terry is leaning over; Causes a knockdown on Counter-Hit / Punish Counter; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',35,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d8d55b93-b03d-4ecd-9029-85287cee7b35','Terry','HP Round Wave','','236HP','special',29,9,14,5,8,900,'L','su3','1-hit stationary projectile hitbox that still counts as a Strike for the purpose of being Perfect Parried, but otherwise functions as a projectile attack; Close-up combo / pressure / oki tool that''s very plus on block; Extended arm hurtbox on frames 38-46 is NOT projectile invincible (after the active frames are finished); No head hurtbox on frames 24-48 while Terry is leaning over; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',36,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6c2cc923-5324-4988-8b63-bd82a42501c2','Terry','OD Power Wave','','236PP','special',15,NULL,28,-2,2,800,'H','su2, su3','2-hit OD projectile; Projectile Speed: 0.055; Travels full-screen; Does not go underneath fireballs (clashes with regular fireballs); Extended arm hurtbox on frames 21-25 is Projectile invincible; No head hurtbox on frames 13-36 while Terry is leaning over; Carries over Counter-Hit / Punish Counter bonus frame advantage to both hits; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state (can pop them up twice in certain juggle combos)',37,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('32087581-246f-47a6-9a28-07878fa6a33c','Terry','LP Quick Burn','','214LP','special',10,2,23,-5,2,900,'H*M','su3','Second hit is an Overhead (effectively 22 frame start-up if the first hit whiffs); Fast but short range special that''s useful for light confirms and maintaining grounded pressure after a light confirm; Leaves Terry in throw range on hit with a +2 strike / throw / shimmy mixup; Cancels into SA3 on the second hit only',38,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7d04a3a0-0bb0-495a-ad67-46dc40fc6dc6','Terry','OD Quick Burn','','214LPMP or LPHP','special',10,2,23,-5,NULL,1400,'H*M','su2, su3','Second hit is an Overhead (effectively 22 frame start-up if the first hit whiffs); Third hit puts opponent into a limited juggle state; Third hit only comes out on HIT; Only SA2/SA3 cancelable on the first 2 hits; Framedata listed refers to the version that plays out on block or whiff (Terry performs an extra knockdown attack on HIT only)',39,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('669ba19b-5ade-4f36-9c76-ae56f85b51c8','Terry','MP Burning Knuckle','','214MP','special',14,9,20,-6,NULL,1000,'H','su3','Faster but shorter range and less active frames compared to the slower HP version (Terry does not lift his arms up at the start for this MP version); Can be plus on block if spaced properly / hitting meaty on later active frame (this gives a screen shake effect to indicate that Terry has the frame advantage); Great tool to close the distance for pressure during the opponents Burnout (the screen does not shake if you are +1~4 on an opponent in Burnout); Grants additional Knockdown advantage on last 2 active frames (even a +42 KD safe jump if last active frame connects on hit); Only cancelable into SA3 (Rising Fang) on the first active frame, cannot be performed from far away',40,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('adfce16a-a461-404a-9697-0a66f3581821','Terry','HP Burning Knuckle','','214HP','special',23,14,17,-8,NULL,1200,'H','su3','Slower but further range and more active frames compared to the faster MP version (Terry lifts up his arms before leaping forward); Can be plus on block if spaced properly / hitting meaty on later active frame (this gives a screen shake effect to indicate that Terry has the frame advantage); Great tool to close the distance for pressure during the opponents Burnout (the screen does not shake if you are +1~4 on an opponent in Burnout); Only cancelable into SA3 (Rising Fang) on active frames 1-5, cannot be performed from far away',41,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6a66614e-fcca-4340-980c-7fd1275fed1e','Terry','OD Burning Knuckle','','214MPHP','special',19,14,17,-8,NULL,1400,'H','su2, su3','Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit; Puts the opponent into a tumbling OTG state on Punish Counter (can follow up with a combo); The tumbling (KD +70~83) can lead into a low wall splat (KD +138~151); Can be plus on block if spaced properly / hitting meaty on later active frame (this gives a screen shake effect to indicate that Terry has the frame advantage); Great tool to close the distance for pressure during the opponents Burnout (the screen does not shake if you are +1~4 on an opponent in Burnout); Cancelable into SA2/SA3 on the first 7 active frames',42,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('08040594-5d24-4450-8340-6289fa2dad62','Terry','LK Crack Shoot','','214LK','special',16,4,4,-3,1,700,'H','','Airborne on frames 7-23 (Forced Knockdown state); Leaps over a lot of attacks; Can be used to switch sides during combos or corpse hop over a knocked down opponent; Not an Overhead; Start-up and active frames shown in parentheses refers to the grounded version (this cannot hit grounded opponents until the 3rd active frame); Causes a spiked knockdown on airborne opponents; Causes a Hard Knockdown (HKD +29) on Punish Counter; Really strong tool against Burnout as well to deal chip damage and stick to the opponent with + frames',43,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('23be0193-8103-445e-9bd9-f9d344422ea7','Terry','MK Crack Shoot','','214MK','special',17,7,2,-3,3,900,'H','','Airborne on frames 9-25 (Forced Knockdown state); Leaps over a lot of attacks (even some standing normals); Can be used to switch sides during combos or corpse hop over a knocked down opponent; Not an Overhead; Start-up and active frames shown in parentheses refers to the grounded version (this won''t hit grounded opponents until the 6th active frame); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Causes a Hard Knockdown (HKD +28) on Counter-hit and Punish Counter; Deals 900 damage to grounded opponents (450 damage on each airborne hit where it hits twice); Really strong tool against Burnout as well to deal chip damage and stick to the opponent with + frames',44,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d50ad5e3-c8a4-41b7-9dd1-1b8d301e1731','Terry','HK Crack Shoot','','214HK','special',23,11,1,-1,NULL,900,'H','','Lower body is projectile invincible on frames 14-31; Airborne on frames 12-34 (Forced Knockdown state); Kicking leg is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 28-30; Leaps over a lot of attacks (even some standing normals); Can be used to switch sides during combos or corpse hop over a knocked down opponent; Final few active frames reach closer to the ground than all other versions of Crack Shoot (can even hit low profile moves meant to avoid your Crack Shoot); Not an Overhead; Start-up and active frames shown in parentheses refers to the grounded version (this won''t hit grounded opponents until the 8th active frame); Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state; Damage is highly variable depending on how you hit the opponent (air or ground) and how often (1-3 times); Deals 1100 damage (300+800) to grounded opponents; There are three different hits in the air that each do 300 damage, and a final hit that deals 800 damage as Terry''s leg kicks down, however it''s not possible to land all of them at the same time, at most you can land two air hits into the final hit, for a total of 1400 damage (but this requires very specific juggle heights); KDA shown refers to when hitting grounded opponents and can be slightly higher when spaced out and hitting on later active frames (KDA is higher and more variable on airborne hits); Really strong tool against Burnout as well to deal chip damage and stick to the opponent with + frames',45,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('78119c25-541c-4f2b-8b33-d5629f724e68','Terry','OD Crack Shoot','','214KK','special',20,4,2,-2,NULL,1200,'H','','Airborne on frames 8-25 (Forced Knockdown state); Leaps over a lot of attacks (even some standing normals); Not an Overhead; Start-up and active frames shown in parentheses refers to the grounded version (this cannot hit grounded opponents until the 2nd active frame); Puts airborne opponents into an OTG limited juggle state; Really strong tool against Burnout as well to deal chip damage and stick to the opponent with + frames',46,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('0e41ce5a-de4a-4e36-8553-d1df73ee0d2e','Terry','LP Rising Tackle','','623LP','special',5,10,21,-23,NULL,1000,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-14; Airborne on frames 6-35 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Terry); Longest air invincibility window and trajectory aiming straight upwards makes this the ideal version for anti-airing jump-ins; Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 300 less damage (700) on active frames 3-10; Only cancelable into SA3 (Rising Fang) on the first active frame (cancel window can be missed when spaced out in combos); Incurs a 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo (like in high hitting anti-air scenarios)',47,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('163c2feb-05c8-4c85-9372-d6e4a0c2b97d','Terry','MP Rising Tackle','','623MP','special',6,4,28,-26,NULL,1200,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-10; Airborne on frames 7-43 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Terry); Trajectory moves forward slightly during start-up making this ideal for anti-airing mid-range jumps; Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 600 less damage (600) on active frames 5-10 (second hit only); Only cancelable into SA3 (Rising Fang) on the first active frame (cancel window can be missed when spaced out in combos); Incurs a 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; First hit has higher juggle limit (6) on active frames 3-4',48,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('1427a635-c0c2-4a4b-989a-76da415269f8','Terry','HP Rising Tackle','','623HP','special',7,2,27,-36,NULL,1300,'H','su3','Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 1-8; Airborne on frames 8-53 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Terry); Great horizontal range makes this ideal for combos/juggles as well as anti-airing jumps from further away; Launches opponent into a limited juggle state; Deals 700 less damage (600) on active frames 3-6 (last 2 hits) or 1000 less damage (300) on active frames 7-20 (last hit only); Last hit whiffs on crouch block resulting in slightly worse block advantage (-40) a bit less chip and drive gauge damage; Only cancelable into SA3 (Rising Fang) on the first active frame (cancel window can be missed when spaced out in combos); Incurs a 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; First hit has higher juggle limit (8) on active frame 2',49,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('24d41e9d-48cd-4eee-8459-ac8bb0684e49','Terry','OD Rising Tackle','','623PP','special',6,2,34,-42,NULL,1600,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-10; Airborne on frames 7-54 (Forced Knockdown state); Cannot hit cross-up (behind Terry); Good horizontal range makes this ideal for combos/juggles as well as anti-airing jumps from further away; Deals less damage when hitting opponents high in the air due to losing out on the earlier hits',50,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b7991d41-981c-4199-8dc3-2cef31e77c1e','Terry','LK Power Charge','','236LK','special',14,5,24,-9,3,700,'H','su3','Keeps the opponent grounded on hit for +3 pressure or even a combo extension (+4 on hit) if slightly spaced out; Can be spaced out during combos / whiff punishes to get higher damaging combo extensions; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state',51,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b9b95c99-d0ee-4c7f-8845-9a2140a470ea','Terry','MK Power Charge','','236MK','special',20,6,23,-11,NULL,800,'H','su3','Puts the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (launches airborne opponents higher than the HK version); +42 KD by itself which can be used for safe jump setups; Can cancel into SA2 (Power Geyser) during the last 4 recovery frames on HIT only (this enables some specific juggle routes)',52,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b1b1b731-99af-446f-a5a7-24fd3986f819','Terry','HK Power Charge','','236HK','special',25,9,27,-16,NULL,800,'H','su3','Cancelable into any other special move on HIT only on frames 26-45 (36F hit confirm window); Cancel window is huge and can be delayed a ton which is often required for optimizing Terry''s combo routes afterwards; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state (grounded opponents get knocked up higher than airborne opponents)',53,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('68fdc26c-e150-45e8-88ca-72a7e3b2159e','Terry','OD Power Charge','','236KK','special',19,8,24,-14,NULL,800,'H','su2, su3','Launches opponent into a wall bounce on hit; Knockdown advantage varies depending on the opponent''s distance from the wall (higher KDA the further away from the wall they are when hit)',54,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('ef19269d-0515-4f84-9408-6e38e296459b','Terry','Buster Wolf','','236236K','super',7,12,60,-26,NULL,2000,'H','','Strike and Throw invincible on frames 1-8; Armor Break; Depletes 0.5 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; Great Reversal and Combo tool with fast start-up and great range (travels ~80% screen length); Puts opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (can juggle into another Buster Wolf if it juggles on later active frames); 15F less recovery frames (45F) on block than on whiff',55,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('5b58046a-2f09-44c2-b4dc-aa11475453ed','Terry','Power Geyser','','214214P','super',13,13,54,-27,NULL,2600,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-17; Invincible to airborne strikes on frames 18-25 (until active frames run out); Armor Break; Depletes 1 Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; 1-hit Super projectile hitbox; Great for combos and juggles as well as a situational anti-air tool; Can be followed up on HIT only with Twin Geyser (costs 3 bars of Drive Gauge), and then again with Triple Geyser (costs another bar of Super meter), resulting in big damage overall; Can also be input with a 21416+P motion for a different visual effect (this version has no actual affect on the properties)',56,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('724a130c-3ba6-4b78-b7f6-d23b6079ebb5','Terry','Twin Geyser','','214214P > 5PP','super',13,13,43,NULL,NULL,3040,'H','','No form of invincibility on this first follow-up hit; This follow-up hit does not deplete any extra Drive Bar on hit for the opponent; Costs 3 extra bars of Drive Gauge to use and can be followed up on HIT only with Triple Geyser (costs another bar of Super Meter); This follow-up can be delayed quite a bit to adjust for the following juggle scenarios; Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state (can be followed up with combo extensions)',57,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('0f2aadf1-95a2-49da-ada8-18160aff8e3b','Terry','Triple Geyser','','214214P > 5PP','super',13,1,125,NULL,NULL,4040,'H','','Fully invincible for the entire duration of this final third hit; Depletes 0,2 extra Drive Bar on hit for the opponent (total of 1,2 Drive Bars); Costs another bar of Super meter to use (total cost being 3 bars of Super); Deals slightly higher base damage by itself than a raw SA3; If Terry attempts to perform this follow-up without having enough Super meter, he will instead perform a feint which leaves him at -3 KD (this wastes his potential juggle follow-ups after Twin Geyser)',58,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('d4ad107c-f55b-4ecd-b48b-75b1319c7274','Terry','Rising Fang','','236236P','super',8,27,29,-50,NULL,4000,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-16; Armor Break; Depletes 1.5 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates 2.1 Drive Bars for Terry; Only goes into the cinematic version if it hits on the first 3 active frames; Deals less damage and doesn''t cause a HKD if it doesn''t go into cinematic version (2650-3000 damage depending on how it hits); Only 3F start-up when canceled into from Rising Tackle / Quick Burn / Burning Knuckle; Last hit whiffs on crouch block resulting in slightly worse block advantage (-53) a bit less chip and drive gauge damage; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials (30% when canceled into from a Rising Tackle combo starter)',59,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('18a36cf8-c452-40f1-9302-4703e1ecf926','Terry','Rising Fang (Critical Art)','','236236P (CA)','super',8,27,29,-50,NULL,4500,'H','','Fully invincible on frames 1-16; Armor Break; Depletes 1.5 Drive Bars on hit for the opponent; Super cinematic time regenerates 2.1 Drive Bars for Terry; Only goes into the cinematic version if it hits on the first 3 active frames; Deals less damage and doesn''t cause a HKD if it doesn''t go into cinematic version (3150-3500 damage depending on how it hits); Only 3F start-up when canceled into from Rising Tackle / Quick Burn / Burning Knuckle; Last hit whiffs on crouch block resulting in slightly worse block advantage (-53) a bit less chip and drive gauge damage; Incurs 10% damage scaling when canceled into from specials (30% when canceled into from a Rising Tackle combo starter); Critical Art does +500 extra damage over regular version',60,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('3447cdd3-d5b7-4440-8b1d-927b2f3a594b','Zangief','Stand LP','','5LP','normal',7,3,9,2,4,400,'H','ch, sp, su','+2 on block is amazing for a jab and sets Zangief up for a true mixup between strike or SPD (command grab); Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; True blockstring when chained into his other light chains; Only 4F start-up when chained into; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; AKA The Credit Card Swipe',1,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('b8c66690-66c7-467b-8989-699c39ba28df','Zangief','Stand MP','','5MP','normal',9,4,17,-2,2,700,'H','tc','Great poke button with decent range and hitboxes, as well as being very easily Counter-hit / Punish confirmable into the MP Target Combo (28F hit confirm window); Only combos into its TC follow-up on Counter Hit, Punish Counter, or when used after Drive Rush; The Flair Chop!',2,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('90bd8bf3-bcdd-4776-8761-b4ab0f1d9ccc','Zangief','Stand HP','','5HP','normal',16,3,22,-3,3,1000,'H','','Normally this move has no armor unless held, however Zangief does get 1-hit of upper-body armor (attacks that hit low enough can go past the armor) on frames 4-6 if Zangief holds the HP button for at least 4-6F before releasing HP (it will still be 16F overall if you release HP before frame 7); The armor for partially held HP is lost immediately upon releasing HP; +2F recovery frames (24F) on whiff; Knocks down opponent on Counter Hit / Punish Counter; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit; Can be held',3,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7f31aab8-0035-46fb-b99d-ada7cc9cb6fa','Zangief','Stand HP (hold)','','5HP (hold)','normal',32,3,22,3,NULL,1400,'H','','1-hit of armor on upper-body on frames 4-34 (attacks that hit low enough can go past the armor); The armor for partially held HP is lost immediately upon releasing HP (followed up with un-armored 10F start-up HP attack); The 10F start-up shown in the parentheses refers to when the HP button is released after holding HP for at least 6 frames; Fully held HP version deals a ton of damage, drive gauge chip as well as give good frame advantage on block makes this a very powerful tool if the opponent doesn''t stop it; Fully held version deals 400 extra damage (1400); +2F recovery frames (24F) on whiff; Causes a +40 Hard Knockdown on Counter-Hit (and a ground slide on Punish Counter for +54 Hard Knockdown)',4,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('88a8cfcf-5d70-4b7c-aea4-fddd860153a3','Zangief','Stand LK','','5LK','normal',7,2,17,-4,-2,400,'H','sp, su','Very far range for a stand LK, although slower than most (slightly further range than his own Stand MP); Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',5,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6762ee09-c1a7-44da-925f-2e38b35d330e','Zangief','Stand MK','','5MK','normal',10,4,19,-4,1,900,'H','','Very good poke button with decent range, strong hitbox priority and very good damage for a MK poke',6,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('06533872-5a09-4df2-95cc-39cd0aa4c0d3','Zangief','Stand HK','','5HK','normal',13,4,21,1,3,1000,'H','','Cannot hit crouching; Zangief''s kicking leg is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 13-22; Good horizontal anti-air (albeit a bit slow start-up); The brief extended leg hurtbox extension 1F before active frames is strike invincible (cannot counter-poke projectiles); Launches opponent into a free juggle state (KD +51) on Punish Counter; Puts airborne opponents into a limited juggle state on hit',7,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('7ef37e8e-472f-4c7c-b39f-1df33a8dbce4','Zangief','Crouch LP','','2LP','normal',6,2,8,1,6,300,'H','ch, sp, su','Plus frames on blocked jab (this is unique to Zangief) and a true blockstring when chained into crouch LP or crouch LK, allowing Zangief to pressure better with his light chains than the rest of the roster; Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; Only 3F start-up when chained into; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-7 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',8,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('c5fbd6c4-761e-4974-9278-754f25c4e0bd','Zangief','Crouch MP','','2MP','normal',8,3,16,-1,3,700,'H','sp, su','Mostly a combo / buffer tool; Topmost hurtboxes on frames 1-7 are vulnerable only to airborne attacks (this is to discourage its use as an anti-air)',9,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('2cc33f90-7075-4270-8e0c-3c39cb6c5891','Zangief','Crouch HP','','2HP','normal',11,9,35,-20,NULL,1000,'H','','Zangief''s head hurtbox is invincible to airborne strikes on frames 10-19 (helps with anti-airing); Good vertical anti-air (but pretty slow start-up); Only the first 3 active frames can hit grounded (the rest only hits airborne aiming above Zangief); Active frames 4-8 (frames 15-19 overall) can hit cross-up (behind Zangief); Launches the opponent into a limited juggle state on hit (Punish Counter launches them higher and into an OTG free juggle state, which Zangief can follow-up with a combo)',10,datetime('now'),datetime('now')),
('6cdad9de-00fc-40df-a40b-b0703da501d8','Zangief','Crouch LK','','2LK','normal',4,3,12,-3,0,250,'L','ch','Zangief''s only 4F normal; Chains into stand LP / crouch LP / crouch LK; True blockstring when chained into crouch LP or crouch LK; Only 3F start-up when chained into; Incurs 20% damage scaling penalty if used as the first hit of a combo',11,datetime('now'),datetime('now'));
